◆ bcm_cosq_bst_multi_profile_get()

int bcm_cosq_bst_multi_profile_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
bcm_bst_stat_id_t  bid,
int  array_size,
bcm_cosq_bst_profile_t *  profile_array,
int *  count 
)

Set/Get the BST profile for CosQ objects.

Similar as bcm_cosq_bst_profile_set and bcm_cosq_bst_profile_get , with the difference that profile can be applied at buffer level. profile_array is an array of BST porfile whose index is buffer id. So an MMU resource identified by port, cosq, and bid can have different profiles on different MMU buffers. Because not all MMU buffers are associated to specified port or cosq, suggest call bcm_cosq_buffer_id_multi_get to know the associated buffers first. array_size is the size of profile array. count returns the actual buffer number of the decive, in "_get" API. In Tomahawk series, follwing BST id can be applied at buffer level:

  • bcmBstStatIdEgrPool
  • bcmBstStatIdEgrMCastPool
  • bcmBstStatIdIngPool
  • bcmBstStatIdPortPool
  • bcmBstStatIdPriGroupShared
  • bcmBstStatIdPriGroupHeadroom
  • bcmBstStatIdMcast
  • bcmBstStatIdEgrPortPoolSharedMcast
Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]gport
[in]cosqCosq object offset identifier
[in]bidBST stat ID to identify the COSQ resource/object
[in]array_sizeMax size of array
[out]profile_array(for "_set") Array of BST profile configuration
(for "_get") Array of BST profile configuration
[out]count(for "_get") Actual size of the profile array

◆ bcm_cosq_bst_profile_get()

int bcm_cosq_bst_profile_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
bcm_bst_stat_id_t  bid,
bcm_cosq_bst_profile_t *  profile 
)

Set/Get the BST profile for CosQ objects.

Configure or retrieve the BST (buffer statistics tracking) configuration for the specified MMU resource. MMU resource is identified by the combination of port, cosq and bid parameters. port parameter can be port gport, queue gport. bid parameter identifies the MMU resource, for instance the bid bcmBstStatIdEgrPool identifies the egress service pool resource. cosq parameter identifies the object within the various instances of resources within the identified resource. Note: For bid=bcmBstStatIdHeadroomPool, returns BCM_E_PARAM as there is no BST configuration required for Headroom Pool The bid parameter can be one of the following from the table

BCM BST CoSQ IDs
flag Description
bcmBstStatIdInvalid Invalid BST Id and used for sync all the Hardware stats to the Software copy
bcmBstStatIdDevice Device wide resource
bcmBstStatIdEgrPool Egress service pool
bcmBstStatIdIngPool Ingress service pool
bcmBstStatIdPortPool Shared pool per port per service pool
bcmBstStatIdPriGroupShared Shared pool per Priority group
bcmBstStatIdPriGroupHeadroom Headroom buffer per Priority group
bcmBstStatIdUcast unicast queue
bcmBstStatIdMcast multicast queue
bcmBstStatIdHeadroomPool Headroom pool
bcmBstStatIdEgrPortPoolSharedUcast Per port pool unicast
bcmBstStatIdEgrPortPoolSharedMcast Per port pool multicast
bcmBstStatIdQueueTotal Generic queue, can be UC/MC or CPU queue.
bcmBstStatIdRQEQueue RQE queue.
bcmBstStatIdRQEPool RQE service pool.
bcmBstStatIdUCQueueGroup Unicast queue group.

If callback function is registered for switch events, BST events will be reported with BID and more detailed information. The parameters in this callback are defined in the following table:

MMU BST Events Callback
arg1 arg2 arg3
bcmBstStatIdDevice -1 -1
bcmBstStatIdEgrPool -1 Service Pool ID
bcmBstStatIdEgrMcastPool -1 Service Pool ID
bcmBstStatIdIngPool -1 Service Pool ID
bcmBstStatIdPortPool Logical port Service Pool ID
bcmBstStatIdPriGroupShared Logical port Priority Group ID
bcmBstStatIdPriGroupHeadroom Logical port Priority Group ID
bcmBstStatIdUcast GPORT COSQ
bcmBstStatIdMcast GPORT COSQ
bcmBstStatIdHeadroomPool -1 Service Pool ID
bcmBstStatIdEgrPortPoolSharedUcast Logical port Service Pool ID
bcmBstStatIdEgrPortPoolSharedMcast Logical port Service Pool ID
bcmBstStatIdRQEQueue -1 RQE queue ID
bcmBstStatIdRQEPool -1 Buffer pool ID
bcmBstStatIdUCQueueGroup Queue Group ID -1
typedef struct bcm_cosq_bst_profile_s {
uint32 byte;
} bcm_cosq_bst_profile_t;
Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]gport
[in]cosqCosq object offset identifier
[in]bidBST stat ID to identify the COSQ resource/object
[out]profileBST profile configuration

◆ bcm_cosq_bst_stat_clear()

int bcm_cosq_bst_stat_clear ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
bcm_bst_stat_id_t  bid 
)

Clear the current statistic/count of specified BST profile.

Clear the BST (buffer statistics tracking) statistic for the specified MMU resource. MMU resource is identified by the combination of port, cosq and bid parameters. port parameter can be port gport, queue gport. bid parameter identifies the MMU resource, for instance the bid bcmBstStatIdEgrPool identifies the egress service pool resource. cosq parameter identifies the object within the various instances of resources within the identified resource. gport value of -1 will clear stats on all ports.

Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]gportDevice or logical port or GPORT ID
[in]cosqCosq object offset identifier
[in]bidBST stat ID to identify the COSQ resource/object

◆ bcm_cosq_bst_stat_sync()

int bcm_cosq_bst_stat_sync ( int  unit,
bcm_bst_stat_id_t  bid 
)

Sync the HW stats value to SW copy for all or given BST resource.

API to sync the Hardware stats for all or given BST resources to the Software copy. During this sync, BST status will be disabled, in order to maintain consistency of the stats to a defined time and Post sync, the BST status will be restored. This is required to be used before calling bst_stat_get() to get latest or updated stats value.

Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]bidBST stat ID to identify the COSQ resource/object

Create a queue classifier.

Create a queue classifier. If the flag BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_WITH_ID is set, classifier_id is an input. When flag BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_FIELD is set then classifier_id is always an output parameter. bcm_cos_queue_t *  cosq_array,
int *  classifier_id 
)

Gets the classifier id for the given profile.

Get the classifier ID for a given profile if it is present else returns BCM_E_NOT_FOUND. User need to calls the bcm_cosq_classifier_id_get for the given profile before calling bcm_cosq_classifier_create. If bcm_cosq_classifier_id_get api returns BCM_E_NOT_FOUND then only bcm_cosq_classifier_create is to be called to get the classifier_id, else the classifier id returned is to be used for mapping profiles and deleting profiles.

◆ bcm_cosq_classifier_t_init()

void bcm_cosq_classifier_t_init ( bcm_cosq_classifier_t *  classifier)

Initialize a bcm_cosq_classifier_t structure.

Initialize a bcm_cosq_classifier_t structure.

typedef struct bcm_cosq_classifier_s {
uint32 flags; // BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_xxx flags
bcm_vlan_t vlan; // VLAN
bcm_mac_t mac; // MAC address
bcm_vrf_t vrf; // Virtual Router Instance
bcm_ip_t ip_addr; // IPv4 address
bcm_ip6_t ip6_addr; // IPv6 address
bcm_gport_t gport; // GPORT ID
uint32 vfi_index; // VFI index
bcm_if_t egress_if; // Egress object interface
} bcm_cosq_classifier_t;

BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER Flags
Name Purpose
BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_WITH_ID Use the specified classifier ID
BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_VLAN Classifier consists of VLAN
BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_L2 Classifier consists of VLAN and MAC address
BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_L3 Classifier consists of VRF and IP address
BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_IP6 The IP address in L3 classifier is IPv6
BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_GPORT Classifier consists of GPORT
BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_FIELD Classifier used in a ingress field processor rule
BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_VFI Classifier consists of VFI index
BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_L3_EGRESS Classifier consists of egress object
BCM_COSQ_CLASSIFIER_NO_INT_PRI Classifier used without internal priority
Parameters
[in,out]classifierPointer to bcm_cosq_classifier_t structure.
Return values
NONE.

◆ bcm_cosq_config_get()

int bcm_cosq_config_get ( int  unit,
int *  numq 
)

Configure the number of Class of Service Queues (COSQs).

Configure or retrieve the number of CoS queues. Different devices support different numbers of queues. 1, 2, 4 or 8 class CoS queues may be configured depending on the underlying device. Configuring the number of CoS queues affects the configuration and utilization of several internal resources in the device. bcm_cosq_config_set configures the device to operate properly for the number of CoS Queues. The CPU CoS queue mapping is also reconfigured to adjust for the numq. For more information regarding user defined CPU CoS queue mappings see bcm_rx_cosq_mapping_set . After configuration of the number of CoS Queues, the application must call bcm_cosq_mapping_set to map the packet priorities into the desired CoS queues. bcm_cosq_config_set configures the mapping to be functional but the priority to CoS Queue mapping is not defined. The number of CoS queues must be configured during system initialization. It is invalid to configure the CoS queues on a system with traffic flowing. The API does not check for this condition and the results are undefined if it occurs. On the chip BCM56960 the default number of CoS queues is 8.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[out]numqNumber of Class of Service Queues
Return values
BCM_E_NONE
BCM_E_UNAVAILRequested number of CoS queues not supported on this device.
BCM_E_XXX

◆ bcm_cosq_control_extended_get()

int bcm_cosq_control_extended_get ( int  unit,
bcm_cosq_object_id_t *  id,
bcm_cosq_control_data_t *  control 
)

Set/get various features at the gport, cosq, and/or other level.

Same as bcm_cosq_control_set and bcm_cosq_control_get, with the difference that features can be controlled on more basis than gport/cosq. In Tomahawk series, follwing features can be controlled at buffer level:

  • bcmCosqControlIngressPortPGSharedLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlIngressPortPGMinLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlEgressPoolSharedLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlEgressPoolResumeLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlEgressPoolYellowSharedLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlEgressPoolYellowResumeLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlEgressPoolRedSharedLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlEgressPoolRedResumeLimitBytes
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]idCompound index containing gport, cosq, buffer, etc. See bcm_cosq_object_id_t_init .
[in,out]control(for "_set") Operation type and corresponding argument. See bcm_cosq_control_data_t_init .
(IN/OUT) (for "_get") Operation type and corresponding argument. The type parameter is an input parameter.

◆ bcm_cosq_control_extended_set()

int bcm_cosq_control_extended_set ( int  unit,
bcm_cosq_object_id_t *  id,
bcm_cosq_control_data_t *  control 
)

Set/get various features at the gport, cosq, and/or other level.

Same as bcm_cosq_control_set and bcm_cosq_control_get, with the difference that features can be controlled on more basis than gport/cosq. In Tomahawk series, follwing features can be controlled at buffer level:

  • bcmCosqControlIngressPortPGSharedLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlIngressPortPGMinLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlIngressHeadroomPoolLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlEgressPoolSharedLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlEgressPoolResumeLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlEgressPoolYellowSharedLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlEgressPoolYellowResumeLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlEgressPoolRedSharedLimitBytes
  • bcmCosqControlEgressPoolRedResumeLimitBytes
  • Note: It is forbidden to configure threshold mixing with single XPE and both XPEs(BCM_COSQ_BUFFER_ID_INVALID) as input parameter buffer ID via bcm_cosq_control_extended_set.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]idCompound index containing gport, cosq, buffer, etc. See bcm_cosq_object_id_t_init .
[in]control(for "_set") Operation type and corresponding argument. See bcm_cosq_control_data_t_init .
(IN/OUT) (for "_get") Operation type and corresponding argument. The type parameter is an input parameter.

◆ bcm_cosq_control_get()

int bcm_cosq_control_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  port,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
bcm_cosq_control_t  type,
int *  arg 
)

Set various features at the gport/cosq level.

Features that can be controlled on a gport/cosq basis. On some devices and for some cosq control types, a port value of -1 or gport type for system configuration will configure system based cosq control.

CoSQ Control Type Values
Value Description Arg value
bcmCosqControlFabricConnectMinUtilization minimum utilization of fabric timeslice, before connection is established percentage of a fabric timeslice. Some chips support values in excess of 100 percent.
bcmCosqControlFabricConnectMaxTime timeout configuration for minimum utilization connection setting timeout is in microseconds.
bcmCosqControlBandwidthBurstMax maximum burst size, use after bcm_cosq_port_bandwidth_set burst size is in kbytes.
bcmCosqControlBandwidthBurstMin maximum burst size for minimum guarantee rate, use after bcm_cosq_port_bandwidth_set burst size is in kbits.
bcmCosqControlFabricConnectMax number of connections that can be retained/held by the queue. count. QE2000: 1-8, BCM88230: 1-16, Default: 2
bcmCosqControlPortTxqBackpressure enable or disable the port capability of pausing traffic scheduling on the specific queue. value 1: enable the pause, 0: disable the pause.
bcmCosqControlCopyPktToCpuUseTC use generic TC based CoS mapping for copying packets to CPU. value 1: Use generic TC based, 0: Use Reason based.
bcmCosqControlWdrrGranularity granularity selector for weighted deficit round robin scheduling. value 1: number of packet, 0: number of 64-bytes.
bcmCosqControlDpValueDlf drop precedence value for unknown unicast/multicast packet. value DLF_DP = 0 ~ 3(DP0 ~ DP3), Default: 2(DP2).
bcmCosqControlDpChangeDlf drop precedence change control for the unknown unicast/multicast packet. value 1: DP=DLF_DP if the packet is a DLF packet, 0: DP is depended on the default port DP.
bcmCosqControlDpChangeXoff drop precedence change control for the flow-controllable port. value 1: DP=DP0, if the port is flow-controllable port, 0: DP is depended on the DLF_DP or the default port DP.
bcmCosqControlEavClassAWindow EAV class A traffic credit carry-over control value 1: the credit carry-over is allowed, 0: the credit carry-over is disabled.
bcmCosqControlEgressRateBurstAccumulateControl burst accumulate control for egress rate. value 1: Enable accumulation, 0: To indicate the value of the Burst Tolerance Size should be reset to zero when there is no packet in the queue waiting to be transmitted.
bcmCosqControlEgressRateType rate type selector for egress rate control. value 1: pkt / sec (100 pkts/sec), 0: bit / sec (64 * 1000 bits/sec).
bcmCosqControlSchedulable Allow TX scheduling of packets in the queue. value 1: Enable scheduling, 0: Disable scheduling.
bcmCosqControlEEETxQCongestionThreshold If the threshold is exceeded, EEE is disabled for all ports. the unit is buffer cell size.
bcmCosqControlPacketLengthAdjust Configures packet length adjustment on a per queue basis. value, positive or negative queue packet length adjustment in bytes
bcmCosqControlFabricPortIngressScheduler Configures ingress scheduler flow control mapping. value, Fabric/Child gport that will be flow control controlled by the specified scheduler node
bcmCosqControlCongestionManagedQueue Congestion managed queue identifier. queue identifier or -1 to disable
bcmCosqControlCongestionFeedbackWeight Congestion feedback weight. value, 0-7
bcmCosqControlCongestionSetPoint Congestion point queue size set point. number of bytes
bcmCosqControlCongestionSampleBytesMin Minimum number of bytes to enqueue between congestion status sampling. sampling interval in bytes
bcmCosqControlCongestionSampleBytesMax Maximum number of bytes to enqueue between congestion status sampling. sampling interval in bytes
bcmCosqControlFlowControlPriority Flow Control Mapping to port level HR end-to-end scheduler. For end-to-end port scheduler only BCM_COSQ_HIGH_PRIORITY value is meaningful for arg parameter.
bcmCosqControlSpLevelMax Retrieve Max SP level of a scheduler Element Only retrieving this configuration is supported
bcmCosqControlSp[0-10]WeightMax For a Scheduler Element, retrieve the Max weight support for SP level [0-10] Only retrieving this configuration is supported
bcmCosqControlFabricPortScheduler Associate a scheduler node with a Fabric/Child Gport value contains fabric/child gport
bcmCosqControlClassMap Associate an Egress Cos (FIFO num) to Multicast EF or Multicast NON-EF. Gport=BCM_GPORT_INVALID for all, value (BCM_COS_MULTICAST_EF, BCM_COS_MULTICAST_NON_EF).
bcmCosqControlSchedulerAdoptAllPriority Scheduler node priority adoption scheme value, 1 - adopt all priorities, 0 - standard behaviour
bcmCosqControlDropLimitAlpha Specified the total number of cells allowed for this FIFO. If the fifo_count plus the packet's cell number is over this limit, the packet will be dropped. FIFO count is dynamic calculated from Drop limit minus buffer count. Equation is: fifo_thresh = alpha * buffers available. Refer to bcmCosqControlDropLimitAlpha Arg table bcm_cosq_control_drop_limit_alpha_value_t for a detailed description of the alpha value.
bcmCosqControlUCDropLimitAlpha bcmCosqControlDropLimitAlpha when applied to Unicast queues. Refer to bcmCosqControlDropLimitAlpha Arg table bcm_cosq_control_drop_limit_alpha_value_t for a detailed description of the alpha value.
bcmCosqControlMCDropLimitAlpha bcmCosqControlDropLimitAlpha when applied to Multicast queues. Refer to bcmCosqControlDropLimitAlpha Arg table bcm_cosq_control_drop_limit_alpha_value_t for a detailed description of the alpha value.
bcmCosqControlDropLimitBytes Specified the total number of cells allowed for this FIFO. If the fifo_count plus the packet's cell number is over this limit, the packet will be dropped. Value:0-0x7FFF.
bcmCosqControlResumeLimitBytes Defines the hysteresis value (FIFO resume value) used to Xon value of the FIFO when the FIFO enters the Xoff (drop) state. The FIFO resume value = FIFO Thresh (determined statically using DropLimitBytes or dynamically using DropLimitAlpha) minus ResumeLimitBytes. If the result is negative, the value will become 0. Value:0-0x7FFF.
bcmCosqControlYellowDropLimitBytes The threshold for 'Yellow' color packet is calculated FIFO thresh (determined above) minus YellowDropLimitBytes. If the result is negative, the threshold will become 0. If the packet is color 'Yellow' and the FIFO count plus the packet's cell number is over this limit, the packet will be dropped. Value:0-0x7FFF.
bcmCosqControlRedDropLimitBytes The threshold for 'Red' color packet is calculated FIFO thresh (determined above) minus RedDropLimitBytes. If the result is negative, the threshold will become 0. If the packet is color 'Red' and the FIFO count plus the packet's cell number is over this limit, the packet will be dropped. Value:0-0x7FFF.
bcmCosqControlEgressPool Egress shared service pool selection for hierarchical mode and non-hierarchical mode. In non-hierarchical mode, it is egress shared service pool selection for MC queue. value, 0-3
bcmCosqControlUCEgressPool Egress shared service pool selection for UC queue in non-hierarchical mode. value, 0-3
bcmCosqControlMCEgressPool Egress shared service pool selection for MC queue in non-hierarchical mode. value, 0-3
bcmCosqControlEgressPoolLimitBytes Shared service pool size. number of bytes
bcmCosqControlEgressYellowPoolLimitBytes Shared service pool size for yellow packets. number of bytes
bcmCosqControlEgressRedPoolLimitBytes Shared service pool size for red packet. number of bytes
bcmCosqControlEgressPoolLimitEnable Enable/disable shared service pool usage check. value: 1 Enable, 0: Disable.
bcmCosqControlEfPropagation Enable/disable EF propagation value: 1 Enable, 0: Disable.
bcmCosqControlFlowControlState Set flow control state. value: FIFO bitmask, bit 0 for FIFO 0 of the port, 1 means not flow controlled, 0 means flow controlled.
bcmCosqControlHeaderUpdateField updating header with queue specific information/signature
bcmCosqControlFlowSlowRate1 configure the device wide slow rate one value:
bcmCosqControlFlowSlowRate2 configure the device wide slow rate two value:
bcmCosqControlFlowSlowRate associate slow rate with a connector gport or scheduling element gport. In case of a composite element this configuration should be done with gport that was returned when the element was added. value: 0 Disable, 1 slow rate one, 2 slow rate two
bcmCosqControlDiscreteWeightLevel0 weight associated with level 0 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute weight configuration
bcmCosqControlDiscreteWeightLevel1 weight associated with level 1 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute weight configuration
bcmCosqControlDiscreteWeightLevel2 weight associated with level 2 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute weight configuration
bcmCosqControlDiscreteWeightLevel3 weight associated with level 3 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute weight configuration
bcmCosqControlAdmissionTestProfileA admission test profile A arg field specified via Admission flags - BCM_COSQ_CONTROL_ADMISSION_[CT | CTTC | CTCC | ST | LLFC | PFC]
bcmCosqControlAdmissionTestProfileB admission test profile B arg field specified via Admission flags - BCM_COSQ_CONTROL_ADMISSION_[CT | CTTC | CTCC | ST | LLFC | PFC]
bcmCosqControlPriorityProfile0 priority profile 0 arg field specifies the profile 0 (Hi/Low priority bitmap)
bcmCosqControlPriorityProfile1 priority profile 1 arg field specifies the profile 1 (Hi/Low priority bitmap)
bcmCosqControlPriorityProfile2 priority profile 2 arg field specifies the profile 2 (Hi/Low priority bitmap)
bcmCosqControlPriorityProfile3 priority profile 3 arg field specifies the profile 3 (Hi/Low priority bitmap)
bcmCosqControlFlowControlEnable Enables / Disables device-level flow control functionality value: 1 Enable, 0: Disable.
bcmCosqControlEgressBandwidthEnable Enable / Disables Egress bandwidth functionality value: 1 Enable, 0: Disable.
bcmCosqControlCongestionFeedbackMax Maximum value of the Congestion Feedback. Units: bytes.
bcmCosqControlCongestionManagedQueueMin It defines the range of VOQs mapped to CP-Id. 0..Number of VOQs.
bcmCosqControlCongestionManagedQueueMax It defines the range of VOQs mapped to CP-Id. 0..Number of VOQs.
bcmCosqControlCongestionThresholdRandom It Randomize the Congestion Sample Threshold. 1 to enable, 0 to disable
bcmCosqControlCongestionProxy Enable QCN Proxy Reaction Point (PRP) function. 1 to enable, 0 to disable
bcmCosqControlSchedulerTxqEmptySelect Select the source of TxQ empty status for round robin scheduler(i.e. WRR/WDRR). value to indicate the source of empty status.
bcmCosqControlBandwidthBurstMaxEmptyQueue Sets the maximum amount of credits that an empty queue can get.
bcmCosqControlBandwidthBurstMaxFlowControlledQueue Sets the maximum amount of credits for a flow controlled queue.
bcmCosqControlSPPortLimitState For each port , retrieve limit state of the corresponding shared pool of the port. 1 indicates limit state set for the shared pool of the port.
bcmCosqControlPGPortLimitState For each port , retrieve limit state of the corresponding priority group of the port. 1 indicates limit state set for the priority group of the port.
bcmCosqControlPGPortXoffState For each port , retrieve xoff state of the corresponding priority group of the port. 1 indicates xoff state set for the priority group of the port.
bcmCosqControlPoolRedDropState For each pool , retrieve drop state of the red packets for the pool. 1 indicates drop state set for red packets for the pool.
bcmCosqControlPoolYellowDropState For each pool , retrieve drop state of the yellow packets for the pool. 1 indicates drop state set for yellow packets for the pool.
bcmCosqControlPoolGreenDropState For each pool , retrieve drop state of the green packets for the pool. 1 indicates drop state set for green packets for the pool.
bcmCosqControlPortQueueUcast According to port and cosq, retrieve hw queue number used by PBSMH UC header hw queue number of PBSMH UC packet headers.
bcmCosqControlPortQueueMcast According to port and cosq, retrieve hw queue number used by PBSMH MC header hw queue number of PBSMH MC packet headers.
bcmCosqControlEgressPortPoolYellowLimitBytes Egress port service pool limit setting for yellow packets. Shared port service pool size for yellow packets.
bcmCosqControlEgressPortPoolRedLimitBytes Egress port service pool limit setting for red packets. Shared port service pool size for red packets.

  • bcmCosqSchedEmptyTxQueue : Empty status from Tx Queue.

◆ bcm_cosq_control_set()

int bcm_cosq_control_set ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  port,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
bcm_cosq_control_t  type,
int  arg 
)

Set various features at the gport/cosq level.

Features that can be controlled on a gport/cosq basis. On some devices and for some cosq control types, a port value of -1 or gport type for system configuration will configure system based cosq control.

CoSQ Control Type Values
Value Description Arg value
bcmCosqControlFabricConnectMinUtilization minimum utilization of fabric timeslice, before connection is established percentage of a fabric timeslice. Some chips support values in excess of 100 percent.
bcmCosqControlFabricConnectMaxTime timeout configuration for minimum utilization connection setting timeout is in microseconds.
bcmCosqControlBandwidthBurstMax maximum burst size, use after bcm_cosq_port_bandwidth_set burst size is in kbytes.
bcmCosqControlBandwidthBurstMin maximum burst size for minimum guarantee rate, use after bcm_cosq_port_bandwidth_set burst size is in kbits.
bcmCosqControlFabricConnectMax number of connections that can be retained/held by the queue. count. QE2000: 1-8, BCM88230: 1-16, Default: 2
bcmCosqControlPortTxqBackpressure enable or disable the port capability of pausing traffic scheduling on the specific queue. value 1: enable the pause, 0: disable the pause.
bcmCosqControlCopyPktToCpuUseTC use generic TC based CoS mapping for copying packets to CPU. value 1: Use generic TC based, 0: Use Reason based.
bcmCosqControlWdrrGranularity granularity selector for weighted deficit round robin scheduling. value 1: number of packet, 0: number of 64-bytes.
bcmCosqControlDpValueDlf drop precedence value for unknown unicast/multicast packet. value DLF_DP = 0 ~ 3(DP0 ~ DP3), Default: 2(DP2).
bcmCosqControlDpChangeDlf drop precedence change control for the unknown unicast/multicast packet. value 1: DP=DLF_DP if the packet is a DLF packet, 0: DP is depended on the default port DP.
bcmCosqControlDpChangeXoff drop precedence change control for the flow-controllable port. value 1: DP=DP0, if the port is flow-controllable port, 0: DP is depended on the DLF_DP or the default port DP.
bcmCosqControlEavClassAWindow EAV class A traffic credit carry-over control value 1: the credit carry-over is allowed, 0: the credit carry-over is disabled.
bcmCosqControlEgressRateBurstAccumulateControl burst accumulate control for egress rate. value 1: Enable accumulation, 0: To indicate the value of the Burst Tolerance Size should be reset to zero when there is no packet in the queue waiting to be transmitted.
bcmCosqControlEgressRateType rate type selector for egress rate control. value 1: pkt / sec (100 pkts/sec), 0: bit / sec (64 * 1000 bits/sec).
bcmCosqControlSchedulable Allow TX scheduling of packets in the queue. value 1: Enable scheduling, 0: Disable scheduling.
bcmCosqControlEEETxQCongestionThreshold If the threshold is exceeded, EEE is disabled for all ports. the unit is buffer cell size.
bcmCosqControlPacketLengthAdjust Configures packet length adjustment on a per queue basis. value, positive or negative queue packet length adjustment in bytes
bcmCosqControlFabricPortIngressScheduler Configures ingress scheduler flow control mapping. value, Fabric/Child gport that will be flow control controlled by the specified scheduler node
bcmCosqControlCongestionManagedQueue Congestion managed queue identifier. queue identifier or -1 to disable
bcmCosqControlCongestionFeedbackWeight Congestion feedback weight. value, 0-7
bcmCosqControlCongestionSetPoint Congestion point queue size set point. number of bytes
bcmCosqControlCongestionSampleBytesMin Minimum number of bytes to enqueue between congestion status sampling. sampling interval in bytes
bcmCosqControlCongestionSampleBytesMax Maximum number of bytes to enqueue between congestion status sampling. sampling interval in bytes
bcmCosqControlFlowControlPriority Flow Control Mapping to port level HR end-to-end scheduler. For end-to-end port scheduler only BCM_COSQ_HIGH_PRIORITY value is meaningful for arg parameter.
bcmCosqControlSpLevelMax Retrieve Max SP level of a scheduler Element Only retrieving this configuration is supported
bcmCosqControlSp[0-10]WeightMax For a Scheduler Element, retrieve the Max weight support for SP level [0-10] Only retrieving this configuration is supported
bcmCosqControlFabricPortScheduler Associate a scheduler node with a Fabric/Child Gport value contains fabric/child gport
bcmCosqControlClassMap Associate an Egress Cos (FIFO num) to Multicast EF or Multicast NON-EF. Gport=BCM_GPORT_INVALID for all, value (BCM_COS_MULTICAST_EF, BCM_COS_MULTICAST_NON_EF).
bcmCosqControlSchedulerAdoptAllPriority Scheduler node priority adoption scheme value, 1 - adopt all priorities, 0 - standard behaviour
bcmCosqControlDropLimitAlpha Specified the total number of cells allowed for this FIFO. If the fifo_count plus the packet's cell number is over this limit, the packet will be dropped. FIFO count is dynamic calculated from Drop limit minus buffer count. Equation is: fifo_thresh = alpha * buffers available. Refer to bcmCosqControlDropLimitAlpha Arg table bcm_cosq_control_drop_limit_alpha_value_t for a detailed description of the alpha value.
bcmCosqControlUCDropLimitAlpha bcmCosqControlDropLimitAlpha when applied to Unicast queues. Refer to bcmCosqControlDropLimitAlpha Arg table bcm_cosq_control_drop_limit_alpha_value_t for a detailed description of the alpha value.
bcmCosqControlMCDropLimitAlpha bcmCosqControlDropLimitAlpha when applied to Multicast queues. Refer to bcmCosqControlDropLimitAlpha Arg table bcm_cosq_control_drop_limit_alpha_value_t for a detailed description of the alpha value.
bcmCosqControlDropLimitBytes Specified the total number of cells allowed for this FIFO. If the fifo_count plus the packet's cell number is over this limit, the packet will be dropped. Value:0-0x7FFF.
bcmCosqControlResumeLimitBytes Defines the hysteresis value (FIFO resume value) used to Xon value of the FIFO when the FIFO enters the Xoff (drop) state. The FIFO resume value = FIFO Thresh (determined statically using DropLimitBytes or dynamically using DropLimitAlpha) minus ResumeLimitBytes. If the result is negative, the value will become 0. Value:0-0x7FFF.
bcmCosqControlYellowDropLimitBytes The threshold for 'Yellow' color packet is calculated FIFO thresh (determined above) minus YellowDropLimitBytes. If the result is negative, the threshold will become 0. If the packet is color 'Yellow' and the FIFO count plus the packet's cell number is over this limit, the packet will be dropped. Value:0-0x7FFF.
bcmCosqControlRedDropLimitBytes The threshold for 'Red' color packet is calculated FIFO thresh (determined above) minus RedDropLimitBytes. If the result is negative, the threshold will become 0. If the packet is color 'Red' and the FIFO count plus the packet's cell number is over this limit, the packet will be dropped. Value:0-0x7FFF.
bcmCosqControlEgressPool Egress shared service pool selection for hierarchical mode and non-hierarchical mode. In non-hierarchical mode, it is egress shared service pool selection for MC queue. value, 0-3
bcmCosqControlUCEgressPool Egress shared service pool selection for UC queue in non-hierarchical mode. value, 0-3
bcmCosqControlMCEgressPool Egress shared service pool selection for MC queue in non-hierarchical mode. value, 0-3
bcmCosqControlEgressPoolLimitBytes Shared service pool size. number of bytes
bcmCosqControlEgressYellowPoolLimitBytes Shared service pool size for yellow packets. number of bytes
bcmCosqControlEgressRedPoolLimitBytes Shared service pool size for red packet. number of bytes
bcmCosqControlEgressPoolLimitEnable Enable/disable shared service pool usage check. value: 1 Enable, 0: Disable.
bcmCosqControlEfPropagation Enable/disable EF propagation value: 1 Enable, 0: Disable.
bcmCosqControlFlowControlState Set flow control state. value: FIFO bitmask, bit 0 for FIFO 0 of the port, 1 means not flow controlled, 0 means flow controlled.
bcmCosqControlHeaderUpdateField updating header with queue specific information/signature
bcmCosqControlFlowSlowRate1 configure the device wide slow rate one value:
bcmCosqControlFlowSlowRate2 configure the device wide slow rate two value:
bcmCosqControlFlowSlowRate associate slow rate with a connector gport or scheduling element gport. In case of a composite element this configuration should be done with gport that was returned when the element was added. value: 0 Disable, 1 slow rate one, 2 slow rate two
bcmCosqControlDiscreteWeightLevel0 weight associated with level 0 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute weight configuration
bcmCosqControlDiscreteWeightLevel1 weight associated with level 1 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute weight configuration
bcmCosqControlDiscreteWeightLevel2 weight associated with level 2 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute weight configuration

bcmCosqControlCongestionFeedbackMax Maximum value of the Congestion Feedback. Units: bytes.

bcmCosqControlEgressMCQueueYellowLimit Specify the Per queue yellow limit for multicast. If color mode dynamic: limit should be between 0-7.If color mode static: Limit is number of bytes.

bcmCosqControlEgressPortPoolRedResumeBytes Resume limit setting for port egress Service Pool for red packets. number of bytes.
bcmCosqControlEgressPortPoolYellowResumeBytes Resume limit setting for port egress Service Pool for yellow packets. number of bytes.
bcmCosqControlEgressPortPoolSharedResumeBytes Resume limit setting for port egress Service pool drop state. number of bytes.
bcmCosqControlIngressPortPoolResumeLimitBytes Ingress Port SP resume limit setting. number of bytes.
bcmCosqControlEgressMCQueueColorLimitEnable Enable Discards based on configured threshold for Egress MC Queue color discard thresholds. 1: MC queue color discard threshold. 0: shared space as discard threshold.
bcmCosqControlEgressUCQueueColorLimitEnable Enable Discards based on configured threshold for Egress UC Queue color discard thresholds. 1: enable UC queue color discard thresholds. 0: disable UC queue color discard thresholds.
bcmCosqControlIngressPortPGGlobalHeadroomEnable: Enable ingress port PG to make use of global Headroom. value: 1 Enable, 0: Disable.

bcmCosqControlMirrorOnDropAgingVsq: Mirror on Drop aging time for vsq type. value:
bcmCosqControlEgressPoolMCSharedLimitEntries: Egress MC Port Pool Shared Limit. value:
bcmCosqControlEgressMCQueueSharedLimitEntries: Egress MC Queue Shared Limit Entries. value:
bcmCosqControlEgressRQESharedLimitBytes: Egress RQE Threshold. value:
bcmCosqControlEgressMCQueueDataBufferSharedLimitBytes: Egress MC Shared Queue limit setting of data buffers in bytes. value:
bcmCosqControlEgressMCQueueDataBufferRedLimit: Specify the Per queue red limit of data buffers for multicast. value:
bcmCosqControlEgressMCQueueEntryRedLimit: Specify the Per queue red limit of egress queue entries for multicast. value:
bcmCosqControlEgressMCQueueDataBufferYellowLimit: Specify the Per queue yellow limit of data buffers for multicast. value:
bcmCosqControlEgressMCQueueEntryYellowLimit: Specify the Per queue yellow limit of egress queue entries for multicast. value:

BCM COSQ DELAY TOLERANCE Configuration
Parameter / Description
credit_request_watchdog_status_msg_gen - Watch Dog Status Message Generation Period. When the Watch Dog Status Message Generation Period time passed since the last credit for an active Queue, the Queue will generate flow status message again. Range: 1 15. (0 disables TH). Resolution: WD full cycle units.
credit_request_watchdog_delete_queue_thresh - Watch Dog Delete Queue Threshold. When the Watch Dog Delete Queue Threshold time passed since the last credit for an active Queue, the Queue will be in Delete State. Range: 100 500. (0 disables TH). Units: milliseconds. Resolution: WD full cycle units.
credit_request_hungry_off_to_slow_thresh - When (QsizeCrBal) > off_to_slow_thresh, and CRS==OFF, CRS may be changed to SLOW. Resolution in bytes. Range: (-114688) - (114688).
credit_request_hungry_off_to_normal_thresh - When (QsizeCrBal) > off_to_normal_thresh, and CRS==OFF, CRS may be changed to NORM. Resolution in bytes. Range: (-114688) - (114688).
credit_request_hungry_slow_to_normal_thresh - When (QsizeCrBal) > slow_to_normal_thresh, and CRS==SLOW, CRS may be changed to NORM. Resolution in bytes. Range: (-114688) - (114688).
credit_request_hungry_normal_to_slow_thresh - When (QsizeCrBal) < normal_to_slow_th, and CRS==NORM, CRS may be changed to SLOW. Resolution in bytes. Range: (-114688) - (114688).
credit_request_hungry_multiplier - When queue size crosses a multiply of multiplier a new FlowStatus Cell is generated. Resolution in bytes. Range: 2^5 2^12. (2^4 disables mechanism).
credit_request_hungry_multiplier - When queue size crosses a multiply of multiplier a new FlowStatus Cell is generated. Resolution in bytes. Range: 2^5 2^12. (2^4 disables mechanism).
credit_request_satisfied_backoff_enter_thresh - When the Credit Balance is bigger than the threshold, the device sends OFF message to the scheduler. This is to prevent credit accumulation from a certain threshold. Resolution in bytes. Range: 0 - 122880.
credit_request_satisfied_backoff_exit_thresh - Hysteresis value for to the Backoff Enter. Resolution in bytes. Range: 0 - 122880.
credit_request_satisfied_backlog_enter_thresh - When the Credit Balance is bigger Backlog Enter threshold bytes than the queue size, the device sends OFF message to the scheduler. This threshold acts as Slow/Norm to off threshold. Resolution in bytes. Range: 0 - 122880.
credit_request_satisfied_backlog_exit_thresh - Hysteresis value for to the Backlog Enter. Resolution in bytes. Range: 0 - 122880.
credit_request_satisfied_backslow_enter_thresh - Hysteresis value for to the Backslow Enter. Resolution in bytes. Range: 0 491520. Resolution: 1 Byte.
credit_request_satisfied_backslow_exit_thresh - Hysteresis value for to the Backslow Exit. Resolution in bytes. Range: 0 491520. Resolution: 1 Byte.
credit_request_satisfied_empty_queue_thresh - When Qsize==0 and CrBal >= satisfied_empty_q_th, the CRS is changed to OFF. This threshold is a specific case of PETRA_ITM_CR_REQUEST_CR_BALANCE_TH. backlog_enter_th threshold. Resolution in bytes. Range: 0 - 122880.
credit_request_satisfied_empty_queue_max_balance_thresh - Max Empty Queue Credit Balance in bytes. This value is the maximum credits an empty queue can accumulate. Resolution in bytes. Range: 0 - 122880.
credit_request_satisfied_empty_queue_exceed_thresh - Exceed Max Empty Queue Credit Balance. This indication permits the credit balance of an empty queue to exceed configured Exceed Max Empty Queue Credit Balance up to (Credit Value minus 1), when a credit is received. This is used to prevent the deletion of partial credits.
flags - Flags from the table below.
slow_level_thresh_up - Seven slow levels thresholds upwards.
slow_level_thresh_down - Seven slow levels thresholds downwards.

flags supported by the flags field of bcm_cosq_delay_tolerance_t
Flag Description
BCM_COSQ_DELAY_TOLERANCE_REMOTE_CREDIT_VALUE specifies for 88660 that the credit value used is not that of the local device; but the other supported credit value used by remote devices.
BCM_COSQ_DELAY_TOLERANCE_IS_LOW_LATENCY Specifies if the delay tolerance is low latency (multiple packet dequeue is enabled).
BCM_COSQ_DELAY_TOLERANCE_HIGH_Q_PRIORITY Specifies that the profile is for high priority queue.
BCM_COSQ_DELAY_TOLERANCE_TOLERANCE_OCB_ONLY Specifies that the profile is for OCB-only queues.
BCM_COSQ_DELAY_TOLERANCE_BANDWIDTH_PROFILE_HIGH Set a queue MAX command credits configurations for high bandwidth traffic.

◆ bcm_cosq_discard_port_get()

int bcm_cosq_discard_port_get ( int  unit,
bcm_port_t  port,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
uint32  color,
int *  drop_start,
int *  drop_slope,
int *  average_time 
)

Configure a port's Weighted Random Early Discard (WRED) parameters.

Configure the port's Weighted Random Early Discard (WRED) parameters. Some vendors do WRED (Weighted Random Early Detection) based on IP precedence per cos, with non-IP packets treated as precedence 0. This implementation does WRED (Weighted Random Early Discard) based on cosq and treats all packets in a queue equally. The parameters are specified for a given port, cosq, and color (green, yellow, or red). A port value of -1 will configure all ports, and a cosq value of -1 will configure all cosq's. The drop start specifies the queue size where drops will begin in terms of percent of max queue size. The drop slope specifies the angle in degrees describing the drop probability slope. The average_time specifies the time in microseconds used in the calculation of average queue depth. This set of APIs is also used for configuring the Simple Random Early Discard (RED) parameters for BCM56224/BCM56514. For a given port, cosq and color, the user can configure the drop_start (percentage of queue size) and the drop probability in increments of one-tenths of a percentage. The drop_slope parameter is overloaded to encode the percentage and must be negative. The average_time parameter is ignored. This set of APIs is also used for configuring the System-RED parameters. System-wide RED control scheme to ensure that on a system level (with multiple devices) color priority will remain. In that case, user should set BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_SYSTEM flag in order to indicate System-RED configuration. In case RED test support more than one slot test. User should set each slot by using flags BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PROBABILITY. Where each flag indicate slot number (first from above). In case RED test support more than one slot test by user set without BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PROBABILITY flags HW configuration assume as there only one slot test. BCM56960 introduces an additional Weighted Curve Set (WCS) profile for ECN Capable transport (ECT). For BCM56960, the packet classifications are for ECT and non-ECT traffic. Non-ECT traffic gets further classified based on congestion control algorithm which reacts to packet drops, into Responsive & Non-Responsive dropping. To support the new WCS profiles, three new packet classification flags have been introduced:

- BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_ECT_MARKED
- BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_RESPONSIVE_DROP
- BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_NON_RESPONSIVE_DROP

The supplied values may be rounded to the nearest value supported by the HW. The available flags for color are BCM_COSQ_COLOR_f

Port Discard Color Flags
Flag Description
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_GREEN Green (default if no color specified)
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_YELLOW Yellow
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_RED Red
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_ALL All Colors
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_DROP_FIRST Alias for BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_RED
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PACKETS discard based on packets. This flag is valid only for BCM5633x, BCM5652x, BCM5662x, BCM5663x, BCM5668x. For other devices, this FLAG should NOT be used.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_BYTES discard based on bytes
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_BUFFER_DESC discard based on buffer descriptors
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_TCP discard based on TCP
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_NONTCP discard based on Non-TCP
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_ECT_MARKED discard based on ECT (ECN capable transport). Transport protocols such as DataCenter TCP (DCTCP), ECT-TCP traffic fall into this category.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_RESPONSIVE_DROP discard based on non-ECT and Responsive Drop. Transport protocols such as TCP-WRED fall into this category.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_NON_RESPONSIVE_DROP discard based on non-ECT and non-Responsive Drop. Transport protocols such as UDP fall into this category.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_SYSTEM System configuration
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PROBABILITY1 discard based on more than one slot. In that case, this flag indicate the upper slot.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PROBABILITY2 discard based on more than one slot. In that case, this flag indicate the lower slot.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portDevice or logical port
[in]cosqCos Queue to configure
[in]colorBCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_*
[out]drop_startPercentage of queue size to start dropping
[out]drop_slopeDegrees 0..90 describing the drop probability slope for WRED. For BCM56224 and BCM56514, this parameter must be negative and each unit describes one-tenths of a percentage of the simple RED drop probability.
[out]average_timeTime in microseconds used in avg queue depth calculation for WRED. For simple RED (BCM56224/BCM56514) this is ignored.

◆ bcm_cosq_discard_port_set()

int bcm_cosq_discard_port_set ( int  unit,
bcm_port_t  port,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
uint32  color,
int  drop_start,
int  drop_slope,
int  average_time 
)

Configure a port's Weighted Random Early Discard (WRED) parameters.

Configure the port's Weighted Random Early Discard (WRED) parameters. Some vendors do WRED (Weighted Random Early Detection) based on IP precedence per cos, with non-IP packets treated as precedence 0. This implementation does WRED (Weighted Random Early Discard) based on cosq and treats all packets in a queue equally. The parameters are specified for a given port, cosq, and color (green, yellow, or red). A port value of -1 will configure all ports, and a cosq value of -1 will configure all cosq's. The drop start specifies the queue size where drops will begin in terms of percent of max queue size. The drop slope specifies the angle in degrees describing the drop probability slope. The average_time specifies the time in microseconds used in the calculation of average queue depth. This set of APIs is also used for configuring the Simple Random Early Discard (RED) parameters for BCM56224/BCM56514. For a given port, cosq and color, the user can configure the drop_start (percentage of queue size) and the drop probability in increments of one-tenths of a percentage. The drop_slope parameter is overloaded to encode the percentage and must be negative. The average_time parameter is ignored. This set of APIs is also used for configuring the System-RED parameters. System-wide RED control scheme to ensure that on a system level (with multiple devices) color priority will remain. In that case, user should set BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_SYSTEM flag in order to indicate System-RED configuration. In case RED test support more than one slot test. User should set each slot by using flags BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PROBABILITY. Where each flag indicate slot number (first from above). In case RED test support more than one slot test by user set without BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PROBABILITY flags HW configuration assume as there only one slot test. BCM56960 introduces an additional Weighted Curve Set (WCS) profile for ECN Capable transport (ECT). For BCM56960, the packet classifications are for ECT and non-ECT traffic. Non-ECT traffic gets further classified based on congestion control algorithm which reacts to packet drops, into Responsive & Non-Responsive dropping. To support the new WCS profiles, three new packet classification flags have been introduced:

- BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_ECT_MARKED
- BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_RESPONSIVE_DROP
- BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_NON_RESPONSIVE_DROP

The supplied values may be rounded to the nearest value supported by the HW. The available flags for color are BCM_COSQ_COLOR_f

Port Discard Color Flags
Flag Description
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_GREEN Green (default if no color specified)
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_YELLOW Yellow
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_RED Red
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_ALL All Colors
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_DROP_FIRST Alias for BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_RED
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PACKETS discard based on packets. This flag is valid only for BCM5633x, BCM5652x, BCM5662x, BCM5663x, BCM5668x. For other devices, this FLAG should NOT be used.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_BYTES discard based on bytes
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_BUFFER_DESC discard based on buffer descriptors
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_TCP discard based on TCP
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_NONTCP discard based on Non-TCP
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_ECT_MARKED discard based on ECT (ECN capable transport). Transport protocols such as DataCenter TCP (DCTCP), ECT-TCP traffic fall into this category.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_RESPONSIVE_DROP discard based on non-ECT and Responsive Drop. Transport protocols such as TCP-WRED fall into this category.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_NON_RESPONSIVE_DROP discard based on non-ECT and non-Responsive Drop. Transport protocols such as UDP fall into this category.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_SYSTEM System configuration
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PROBABILITY1 discard based on more than one slot. In that case, this flag indicate the upper slot.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PROBABILITY2 discard based on more than one slot. In that case, this flag indicate the lower slot.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portDevice or logical port
[in]cosqCos Queue to configure
[in]colorBCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_*
[in]drop_startPercentage of queue size to start dropping
[in]drop_slopeDegrees 0..90 describing the drop probability slope for WRED. For BCM56224 and BCM56514, this parameter must be negative and each unit describes one-tenths of a percentage of the simple RED drop probability.
[in]average_timeTime in microseconds used in avg queue depth calculation for WRED. For simple RED (BCM56224/BCM56514) this is ignored.

)

Update one rule in a profile.

Update one rule in a profile. A discard rule is composed of conditions and action. See BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_RULE_table . A discard profile is composed of a set of rules to cover all possible conditions. When the device state matches to the conditions of one of the rules, the rule's discard action takes effect.

BCM CoSQ Discard Rules
Parameter Description
egress_pool_congestion_state Discard conditions: pool congestion state. See table BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_CONGESTION_table
queue_min_congestion_state Discard conditions: Queue/Qgroup min use state. See table BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_CONGESTION_table
action Discard action. See table BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_ACTION_table

BCM CoSQ Congestion State
Value Description
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_CONGESTION_LOW Pool is high congested, or Queue/Qgroup min is used up.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_CONGESTION_MEDIUM Pool is medium congested.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_CONGESTION_HIGH Pool is low congested, or Queue/Qgroup min is available.

BCM CoSQ Discard Action
Value Description
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_ACTION_WRED_DROP WRED discard.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_ACTION_FORCE_DROP Force discard all packets.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_ACTION_FORCE_NO_DROP Force not discard any packets.

◆ bcm_cosq_ebst_control_get()

int bcm_cosq_ebst_control_get ( int  unit,
bcm_cosq_ebst_control_t  type,
int *  arg 
)

Set/Get EBST scan interval, scan mode and enable mode.

Before starting the EBST scan, user must select the type of resource the EBST engine would scan. The following is a list of possible scan modes, each corresponding to a resource type. Queues Unicast Port Service Pool Multicast Port Service Pool A change in scan mode is only supported after completely stopping the EBST scan. Background engine scan time should be configured. The minimum value of this configuration should be greater than the worst case scan around duration. The worst case scan around duration is defined as Time to scan all configured EBST nodes + Time to read all configured EBST nodes. During EBST tracking EBST scan can be stop or start without disable EBST tracking. If callback function is registered for switch events. Switch event BCM_SWITCH_EVENT_MMU_EBST_FIFO_FULL in switch_events will be reported. The parameters in this callback are defined in the following table:

MMU EBST Events Callback
arg1 arg2 arg3
buffer id -1 -1

This switch event occurs when the switch EBST FIFO gets full. It is indicative of incorrect EBST scan interval configuration which may need further adjustments. The EBST_FIFO_FULL condition can be recovered by increase EBST scan interval and call bcmCosqEbstControlScanEnable to start EBST scan again.

Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]typeEbst control type : bcm_cosq_ebst_control_t.
[out]arg(IN/OUT) control value

◆ bcm_cosq_ebst_data_get()

int bcm_cosq_ebst_data_get ( int  unit,
bcm_cosq_object_id_t *  object_id,
bcm_bst_stat_id_t  bid,
int  array_size,
bcm_cosq_ebst_data_entry_t *  entry_array,
int *  count 
)

Get EBST stat for a given stat Id.

When EBST is enabled, a background hardware process scans the BST counters periodically. If BST count crosses the start threshold of a particular BST counter (queue / PortSP), it copies the occupancy level information to EBST Data buffer per ITM. This information includes the timestamp of the scan and the buffer count in cells. To read the records, recommend to stop monitor for a EBST resource or stop EBST scan. The records will be not keep during warmboot and will be cleared when EBST disable. The bid parameter can be one of table BCM_EBST_BST_COSQ_table . Note: to use this api the buffer_id in object_id should be specified.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]object_idCompound index containing gport, cosq, buffer, etc. See bcm_cosq_object_id_t_init
[in]bidBST stat ID to identify the COSQ resource/object
[in]array_sizeArray size
[out]entry_arrayEntry array
[out]countArray Count

◆ bcm_cosq_ebst_monitor_get()

int bcm_cosq_ebst_monitor_get ( int  unit,
bcm_cosq_object_id_t *  object_id,
bcm_bst_stat_id_t  bid,
bcm_cosq_ebst_monitor_t *  monitor 
)

Set/Get monitor info for a given BST stat Id.

EBST FIFO entries are DMAd to the host memory by the CMIC. The EBST Data buffer is defined as a common shared pool per MMU buffer which each of the EBST resource (port SP and queues) can be used to store the entries. The resource that the user intends to monitor should be configured to reserve a block of contiguous indices in the EBST data buffer. The block size for each EBST Data buffer should be same. To avoid fragmentation, the block size can not be changed during EBST enable. Data buffer read/write meanwhile could lead to inconsistencies in the data buffer. To avoid this possibility, monitor enable was used to disable the resource from an EBST scan. The bid parameter can be one of table BCM_EBST_BST_COSQ_table

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]object_idCompound index containing gport, cosq, buffer, etc. See bcm_cosq_object_id_t_init
[in]bidBST stat ID to identify the COSQ resource/object
[out]monitor(IN/OUT) EBST monitor info structure

◆ bcm_cosq_ebst_threshold_profile_get()

int bcm_cosq_ebst_threshold_profile_get ( int  unit,
bcm_cosq_object_id_t *  object_id,
bcm_bst_stat_id_t  bid,
bcm_cosq_ebst_threshold_profile_t *  profile 
)

Set/Get a EBST threshold profile for a given BST stat Id.

EBST has a profile based start and stop threshold configuration. When a micro-burst occurs in the TM buffers and the corresponding BST count crosses the start threshold, the event is captured and recorded in the switch FIFO. The periodic hardware scan would continue capturing the buffer utilization levels until count falls below the stop threshold. This collection of records in the switch FIFO provides the application a comprehensive picture of the micro-burst. Each EBST resource (queue or PortSP) has a pointer to this profile. The bid parameter can be one of the following from the table BCM_EBST_BST_COSQ_table

BCM EBST BST CoSQ IDs
flag Description
bcmBstStatIdUcast unicast queue
bcmBstStatIdMcast multicast queue
bcmBstStatIdEgrPortPoolSharedUcast Per port pool unicast
bcmBstStatIdEgrPortPoolSharedMcast Per port pool multicast
Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]object_idCompound index containing gport, cosq, buffer, etc. See bcm_cosq_object_id_t_init
[in]bidBST stat ID to identify the COSQ resource/object
[out]profile(IN/OUT) EBST profile configuration

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_add()

int bcm_cosq_gport_add ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  port,
int  numq,
uint32  flags,
bcm_gport_t *  gport 
)

Allocate/Retrieve unicast queue group and scheduler queue group configuration.

These APIs are used to allocate/retrieve unicast or multicast queue group or a scheduler queue group configuration. Scheduler queue groups are used to implement H-QoS. The set of CoS queues are uniquely identified with a GPORT ID, which represents the base CoS queue in the set. The GPORT ID is allocated from the next available queue in group of queues for the port or specified by the input when the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_ID flag is set. But the flag BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_ID is only supported for a few devices. BCM_GPORT_TYPE_UCAST_QUEUE_GROUP, BCM_GPORT_TYPE_MCAST_QUEUE_GROUP, or BCM_GPORT_TYPE_SCHEDULER type of GPORT can be added for hierarchical queuing (see also, bcm_cosq_gport_attach API). Depending on the functionality physical_port parameter can have one of the following values

  • unicast queue group => BCM_GPORT_MODPORT_SET()
  • multicast queue group => BCM_GPORT_MODPORT_SET()
  • scheduler queue group => BCM_GPORT_NULL When allocating a queue group the req_gport parameter direction depends on the flags. If BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_ID is specified the input direction is valid. Depending on the functionality the following macros can be used to create the req_gport.
  • unicast queue group => BCM_GPORT_UCAST_QUEUE_GROUP_SET()
  • multicast queue group => BCM_GPORT_MCAST_QUEUE_GROUP_SET()
  • scheduler queue group => BCM_GPORT_SCHEDULER_SET() req_gport parameter is always updated and should be subsequently used by the user. When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_ID flag is set, the value provided in the gport parameter is used as the GPORT ID, otherwise a unique GPORT ID will be allocated and returned. The feature using BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_ID to allocate a queue group is only supported for a few devices. For some devices that may not have the ability to shape every port or queue, the application can control whether the gport must be allocated from a shapeable or non-shapeable area. This can be done by specifying the flags BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_SHAPING or BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITHOUT_SHAPING, respectively. If neither flag is specified, the API will allocate a gport without paying any attention to whether it would be possible to configure a shaper on such port later. When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_OVERLAY flag is set, it allows overlay of queues that were previously allocated. When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_SUBSCRIBER flag is set, scheduling for the queue group will be done locally and will not involve the central arbiter. A local gport should be added only for ports which are local to that device. When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_MULTIPATH flag is set, a multipath shaper gport is created. Scheduler nodes on the same level could be added to the multipath shaper gport. The aggregated traffic from all nodes is shaped by the multipath shaper. The shaping rate of multipath shaper is controlled by calling bcm_cosq_gport_bandwidth_set API with the multipath shaper gport When the config.bcm variable "fabric_egress_setup=0" is set, FIFO-level egress support becomes available. The BCM_COSQ_GPORT_EGRESS_GROUP flag is used to enable egress group support. Egress Group gports are similar to egress child gports in all other aspects. The egress group gport connects a number of FIFOs to a subport and allows access at the FIFO-level. Multiple egress groups can be connected to the same subport up to sixteen FIFOs. In the case of egress gports, the num_cos_levels field is used to indicate the number of FIFOs to be associated with that egress gport. When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_DESTMOD_UCAST_QUEUE_GROUP flag is set, a set of virtual queue group (DMVOQ) is allocated. On BCM5645X chips, When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_DESTMOD_UCAST_QUEUE_GROUP flag is used with the combination of BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_ID, the value provided in gport parameters is used as the GPORT_ID. But scheduling mode need to programmed again as per the scheduling hierarchy. API bcm_cosq_port_sched_set() can be used to set the scheduling mode to be Strict/WRR. When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_VLAN_UCAST_QUEUE_GROUP flag is set, a queue to support service based queuing is allocated When a parent node is created by using bcm_cosq_gport_add API call by passing num_cos_levels = -1 then that node can have any number of child nodes. On the chips BCM5686x/BCM5685x/BCM56750/BCM56830/BCM5664x/BCM5604x/BCM5634x/BCM5654x, default schedule hierarchies are set up at SDK initialization. Default schedule hierarchy elements cannot be managed except using non-gport APIs to configure COSQs at port level. The first call to the API bcm_cosq_gport_add will destroy the default schedule hierarchies for all of ports and traffic will not flow on those ports until new schedule hierarchies for those ports are built. On the chips BCM56960 and BCM56870 API bcm_cosq_gport_add return BCM_E_PARAM because of fixed hierarchy. Gport tree is created during init. On the chips BCM56960 and BCM56870 because of fixed hierarchy scheduler the scope of COSQ GPORT is not global but it is local to per unit. So we should not modify the MODID dynamically. Some device configuration support multiple queue groups on a physical port.

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_attach()

int bcm_cosq_gport_attach ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  sched_port,
bcm_gport_t  input_port,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq 
)

Attach/Detach the output of a GPORT to the input of a scheduler GPORT.

These APIs can be used to attach/detach a sched GPORT (sched_port) to the parent GPORT (input_port) to form a queuing hierarchy. The connect is done at the specified CoS queue of the parent GPORT. A cosq value of -1 will attach the sched GPORT to the first unused CoS queue of the parent GPORT (going from higher to lower CoS queue priority). On chips BCM56850/BCM56860: When attach new scheduler node to a port's scheduling tree, it is required to allocate contiguous node indices for all these scheduler nodes. Previous allocated scheduling tree will be detached firstly and attached to reassigned scheduling node indices and theirs sibling and children will be reattached if there are no contiguous node indices to accommodate both previously allocated and new requesting nodes. During this all theirs sibling and children nodes will be set to WRR mode with weight 1. On the chip BCM56960: bcm_cosq_gport_attach_get can be used to get the parent node gport and cosq value will represent the CoS queue value of the parent node i.e. the index at which parent is attached. bcm_cosq_gport_attach and bcm_cosq_gport_detach APIs are only supported for CPU port. CPU Queues needed to be mapped to CMC0 Channel 0 should be attached to 3rd index of L0 level scheduler node of CPU port. CPU Queues needed to be mapped to CMC0 Channel 1 should be attached to 0th index of L0 level scheduler node of CPU port. CPU Queues needed to be mapped to CMC0 Channel 2 should be attached to 1st index of L0 level scheduler node of CPU port. CPU Queues needed to be mapped to CMC0 Channel 3 should be attached to 2nd index of L0 level scheduler node of CPU port. CPU Queues needed to be mapped to CMC1 Channel 1 should be attached to 7th index of L0 level scheduler node of CPU port. CPU Queues needed to be mapped to CMC2 Channel 1 should be attached to 8th index of L0 level scheduler node of CPU port. And CPU Queues after detach using bcm_cosq_gport_detach API will get attached to 9th index of L0 level scheduler node CPU port. On the chip BCM56880: CPU Queues after detach using bcm_cosq_gport_detach API will get attached to 11th index of L0 level scheduler node(L0.11 is reserved) CPU port.

Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]sched_portGPORT ID that gets attached to input_port
[in]input_port(IN/OUT) GPORT ID to which sched_port gets attached
[in]cosq(IN/OUT) CoS queue to attach to

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_bandwidth_get()

int bcm_cosq_gport_bandwidth_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
uint32 *  kbits_sec_min,
uint32 *  kbits_sec_max,
uint32 *  flags 
)

Configure/Retrieve bandwidth setting.

Configure/retrieve bandwidth setting. If BCM_COSQ_ALL is specified the configuration applies to the entire queue group. On some devices, the bandwidth allocated to each CoS queue may be configured. The gport parameter can be a physical port, in which case the CoS queue specified by the cosq parameter is one of the default CoS queues assigned to the port during initialization. Alternatively, the gport parameter can be a GPORT that was dynamically added with bcm_cosq_gport_add or bcm_cosq_fabric_distribution_add . In this case, the GPORT ID represents the base CoS queue and the cosq parameter identifies the specific CoS queue as an offset from the base. For the chip BCM5645x if the GPORT ID is a Scheduler GPORT, cosq parameter identifies the specific child attached to the CoS value of the scheduler GPORT. If the GPORT ID is a CoS queue GPORT, GPORT represents the absolute CoS queue and the cosq parameter has no significance. For the chip BCM5645x, there are no flags supported. Hence the parameter flags must be set to 0. The maximum bandwidth setting is applicable to any mode on these devices. However, for non-XCore (tm) and non-XGS devices, the minimum bandwidth settings and the preference flags are only valid when the WEIGHTED_FAIR_QUEUING mode is selected. The order of the calls bcm_cosq_gport_bandwidth_set and bcm_cosq_gport_sched_set is not important. For certain non-XCore (tm) devices(e.g., BCM5685x/BCM5686x) cosq value of -1 will configure all cosq's, while for others(e.g., BCM5687x/BCM5688x/BCM5696x/BCM5697x/BCM5698x/BCM5699x) BCM_E_PARAM would be yielded. The supplied bandwidth values may be rounded up to the nearest value supported by the HW.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]gportGPORT ID for a queue group
[in]cosqCoS Queue
[out]kbits_sec_min(for "_set") CIR (Bandwidth guarantee)
(for "_get") CIR (Bandwidth guarantee)
[out]kbits_sec_max(for "_set") PIR (Traffic shaping)
(for "_get") PIR (Traffic shaping)
[out]flags(for "_set") Specifies bandwidth configuration. Can be logical OR of of values defined in table BCM_COSQ_BW_f
(IN/OUT) (for "_get") specifies bandwidth configuration.

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_color_size_get()

Configure/retrieve minimum and maximum queue depth color based size setting.

Configure/retrieve color based size setting.

size flags
COSQ_GPORT_SIZE_BYTES size setting units are bytes
COSQ_GPORT_SIZE_BUFFER_DESC size setting units are buffer descriptors
COSQ_GPORT_SIZE_COLOR_BLIND size setting is color blind
COSQ_GPORT_SIZE_COLOR_SYSTEM_RED Set system red color. color parameter will represent System red value.
COSQ_GPORT_SIZE_VSQ_OCB_ONLY Configure the OCB-only VSQ, else configure the Dram-mix VSQ.
COSQ_GPORT_SIZE_SRC_VSQ_POOL1 Configure the pool-1 source VSQ, else configure the pool-0 source VSQ.
COSQ_GPORT_SIZE_SRAM Configure SRAM values.
COSQ_GPORT_SIZE_PACKET_DESC Configure packet description.

size configuration
Parameter Description
size_min minimum (guaranteed) size
size_max maximum size
size_alpha_max for specific devices only: queue size will not exceed (free size)*2^size_alpha_max
size_fadt_min for specific devices only: minimal value (mostly for FADT)
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_congestion_config_get()

int bcm_cosq_gport_congestion_config_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
bcm_cosq_congestion_info_t *  config 
)

Set/Get properties for the queue gport.

These API sets and gets the congestion related configuration for queues. Some types of queues, specifically DPVOQ (Destination Port VOQ) and DMVOQ (destination module VOQ), which enable to manage congestion based on destination module or destination module/Port, require more information not only for packet forwarding but also to react to congestion messages in a chassis based system. For instance DMVOQ queues need to know the virtual queue they represent specified by dest_modid parameter of the config structure. Similarly DPVOQ queues need to know the destination module and destination po rt they represent.

typedef struct bcm_cosq_congestion_info_s {
bcm_module_t fabric_modid; // Fabric module ID.
bcm_port_t fabric_port; // Fabric module ID.
bcm_module_t dest_modid; // destination module ID.
bcm_port_t dest_port; // destination port ID.
} bcm_cosq_congestion_info_t;
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]gportQueue GPORT ID
[in]cosqCoS queue to attach to
[out]config(IN/OUT) Congestion configuration

attaches VoQ connector to the VoQ

This API attaches VoQ connector to the VoQ on egress and attaches VoQ to VoQ connector on Ingress.

Connection flags
BCM_COSQ_GPORT_CONNECTION_INGRESS establishing the connection on ingress
BCM_COSQ_GPORT_CONNECTION_EGRESS establishing the connection on egress
BCM_COSQ_GPORT_CONNECTION_INVALID removing the connection

BCM COSQ GPORT Connection Configuration
Parameter Description
flags connection flags. see table BCM_COSQ_GPORT_CONNECTION_flags
remote_modid remote module id.
voq voq gport. On a "_get" operation this parameter is specified for Ingress and retrieved for Egress. see table BCM_COSQ_GPORT_CONNECTION_flags
voq_connector voq connector gport. On a "_get" operation this parameter is specified for Egress and retrieved for Ingress except for the 'core' field, which is supposed to be specified by the caller. Currently, expected values for 'core' are: either '0' or '1'. Note that, on Egress, this procedure assumes 'core' field has been set properly by the caller. ◆ bcm_cosq_gport_detach()

int bcm_cosq_gport_detach ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  sched_port,
bcm_gport_t  input_port,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq 
)

Attach/Detach the output of a GPORT to the input of a scheduler GPORT.

These APIs can be used to attach/detach a sched GPORT (sched_port) to the parent GPORT (input_port) to form a queuing hierarchy. The connect is done at the specified CoS queue of the parent GPORT. A cosq value of -1 will attach the sched GPORT to the first unused CoS queue of the parent GPORT (going from higher to lower CoS queue priority). On chips BCM56850/BCM56860: When attach new scheduler node to a port's scheduling tree, it is required to allocate contiguous node indices for all these scheduler nodes. Previous allocated scheduling tree will be detached firstly and attached to reassigned scheduling node indices and theirs sibling and children will be reattached if there are no contiguous node indices to accommodate both previously allocated and new requesting nodes. During this all theirs sibling and children nodes will be set to WRR mode with weight 1. On the chip BCM56960: bcm_cosq_gport_attach_get can be used to get the parent node gport and cosq value will represent the CoS queue value of the parent node i.e. the index at which parent is attached. bcm_cosq_gport_attach and bcm_cosq_gport_detach APIs are only supported for CPU port. CPU Queues needed to be mapped to CMC0 Channel 0 should be attached to 3rd index of L0 level scheduler node of CPU port. CPU Queues needed to be mapped to CMC0 Channel 1 should be attached to 0th index of L0 level scheduler node of CPU port. CPU Queues needed to be mapped to CMC0 Channel 2 should be attached to 1st index of L0 level scheduler node of CPU port. CPU Queues needed to be mapped to CMC0 Channel 3 should be attached to 2nd index of L0 level scheduler node of CPU port. CPU Queues needed to be mapped to CMC1 Channel 1 should be attached to 7th index of L0 level scheduler node of CPU port. CPU Queues needed to be mapped to CMC2 Channel 1 should be attached to 8th index of L0 level scheduler node of CPU port. And CPU Queues after detach using bcm_cosq_gport_detach API will get attached to 9th index of L0 level scheduler node CPU port. On the chip BCM56880: CPU Queues after detach using bcm_cosq_gport_detach API will get attached to 11th index of L0 level scheduler node(L0.11 is reserved) CPU port.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]sched_portGPORT ID that gets attached to input_port
[in]input_port(IN/OUT) GPORT ID to which sched_port gets attached
[in]cosq(IN/OUT) CoS queue to attach to

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_discard_get()

int bcm_cosq_gport_discard_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
bcm_cosq_gport_discard_t *  discard 
)

Configure/Retrieve discard setting.

Configures discard/WRED setting. The port parameter can be a physical port, in which case the CoS queue specified by the cosq parameter is one of the default Cos queues assigned to the port during initialization. Alternatively, the port parameter can be a GPORT that was dynamically added with bcm_cosq_gport_add or bcm_cosq_fabric_distribution_add . In this case, the GPORT ID represents the base CoS queue and the cosq parameter identifies the specific CoS queue as an offset from the base. The base CoS queue should be UC queue GPORT or port GPORT. For non-XCore devices, if the cosq value is -1, then the discard parameters are applied to the per-port discard settings. If the port parameter is set to BCM_GPORT_INVALID, then the discard parameters are applied to the device-wide discard settings. For the Northstar-Plus devices, if the flag, BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_IFP, is set, then the input discard parameters are applied to the device-wide default WRED configuration. This configuration will be used when the IFP action, bcmFieldActionUseDefaultWred, is set. On the chips BCM56850/BCM56860/BCM56960, bcm_cosq_gport_discard_get will return BCM_E_PARAM when flag BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PACKETS is specified. It assumes it is BYTE mode if both flags BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_BYTES and BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PACKETS are not specified. For bcm_cosq_gport_discard_set, in case none of the COLOR flags is specified, it assumes it is ALL COLOR mode. Discard configuration is listed in the following tables. BCM_COSQ_GPORT_DISCARD_table

BCM CoSQ GPORT Discard Configuration
Parameter Description
flags discard flags. see table BCM_COSQ_GPORT_DISCARD_f
min_thresh Queue depth to begin dropping
max_thresh Queue depth to drop all packets
drop_probability Drop probability at max threshold. Defining a drop probability of zero disables WRED/discard functionality.
gain Determines the smoothing that should be applied to drop probability calculation. Smoothing is achieved by taking into account the drop probability history.
ecn_thresh Queue depth to stop marking start dropping ECN eligible packets
refresh_time Actual average refresh time
use_queue_group whether use QGroupMin instead of QMin for WRED decision
profile_id profile of discard rules, see bcm_cosq_discard_profile_create and bcm_cosq_discard_profile_update . On chip BCM56880, profile_id will only take affect when discard is configured on queue.

Some of the option flags can be logically OR'ed.

gport Discard Color Flags
Flag Description
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_ENABLE Enable Discard (WRED) functionality.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_CAP_AVERAGE Never let average queue size be bigger than actual queue size. Valid for non-XCore devices.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_GREEN Green
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_YELLOW Yellow
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_RED Red
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_BLACK Black
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_ALL All Colors
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_DROP_FIRST Alias for BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_RED.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_BYTES Configure BYTE thresholds.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PACKETS Configure PACKET thresholds. Valid for non-XCore devices.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_MARK_CONGESTION Mark ECN instead of dropping
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PORT Configure per-port thresholds. In Tomahawk series it takes effect only when Discard is enabled on both port and queue.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_DEVICE Configure per-device thresholds. In Tomahawk series it takes effect only when Discard is enabled on both device and queue.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_IFP Configure the default WRED profile that is used for IFP action.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_OUTER_CFI CFI value of the outer tag.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_VSQ_OCB_ONLY Configure the OCB-only VSQ, else configure the Dram-mix VSQ.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_TCP Used for setting discard thresholds for TCP traffic.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_NONTCP discard based on Non-TCP
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_ECT_MARKED discard based on ECT (ECN capable transport). Combined use with BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_MARK_CONGESTION. Transport protocols such as DataCenter TCP (DCTCP), ECT-TCP traffic fall into this category.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_NON_RESPONSIVE_DROP discard based on non-ECT and non-Responsive Drop. Combined use with BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_NONTCP. Transport protocols such as UDP fall into this category.
BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_RESPONSIVE_DROP discard based on non-ECT and Responsive Drop. Combined use with BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_TCP. Transport protocols such as TCP-WRED fall into this category.

BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_COLOR_ALL is not a valid color value for retrieving discard configuration. Discard is configured on queue if neither BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_PORT nor BCM_COSQ_DISCARD_DEVICE is set. The discard parameters consist of min and max thresholds, which define the start and end range (in bytes or packets) where packets may get discarded. When the average queue size is below the min threshold, no packets will be discarded. The drop_probability parameter can be used to specify the drop probability at the max threshold. When the average queue size is between the min and max threshold, the drop probability increases linearly from zero percent (at the min threshold) to drop_probability percent (at the max threshold). When the average queue size is greater than the max threshold, all packets are discarded.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]gportGPORT ID for a queue group
[in]cosqCoS Queue
[in,out]discard(for "_set") discard configuration
(IN/OUT) (for "_get") discard configuration, see table BCM_COSQ_GPORT_DISCARD_table . the flags parameter is an input parameter.

Configure or retrieve the mapping from the internal priority value to Cos for egress queues. The internal priority is usually initialized from the packet priority. ◆ bcm_cosq_gport_egress_multicast_config_get()

int bcm_cosq_gport_egress_multicast_config_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,

Configure/retrieve {traffic class, dp} mapping to multicast egress configuration on a port.

Configure/retrieve {traffic class, dp} mapping to multicast egress configuration on a port. The gport identifies the underlying resource. The resource will be local gport. When gport is local port, flags should be BCM_COSQ_MULTICAST_SCHEDULED, and only scheduled fields of "bcm_cosq_egress_multicast_config_t" structure are valid. When gport is null, flags should be BCM_COSQ_MULTICAST_UNSCHEDULED, and only unscheduled fields of "bcm_cosq_egress_multicast_config_t" structure are valid. Gport parameter identifies the mapping to be for scheduled multicast or unscheduled multicast. The "flags" parameter is redundant. However the flag value identifies what fields of "bcm_cosq_egress_multicast_config_t" structure are valid.

// Multicast configuration settings
typedef struct bcm_cosq_egress_multicast_config_s {
bcm_color_t scheduled_dp; // drop precedence
bcm_cos_t priority; // traffic class
int unscheduled_se; // shared resource eligibility
int unscheduled_sp; // service pool ID
} bcm_cosq_egress_multicast_config_t;

multicast service pools id's
bcmCosqEgressMulticastServicePool0 Service pool 0 identifier
bcmCosqEgressMulticastServicePool1 Service pool 1 identifier
Parameters
[in]unit[IN] BCM device number
[in]gport[IN] gport referencing unicast or multicast egress queues on a port
[in]ingress_pri[IN] packet priority/traffic class
[in]ingress_dp[IN] packet drop precedence
[in]flags[IN] Specifies configuration. Valid flags: BCM_COSQ_MULTICAST_SCHEDULED, BCM_COSQ_MULTICAST_UNSCHEDULED
[out]config[IN] (for "_set") multicast egress configuration
[OUT] (for "_get") multicast egress configuration
