Configure/retrieve mapping of fabric egress cos level to front panel cos level.

This API sets the mapping of fabric egress cos level to front panel cos level. The front panel cos level corresponds to Packet Processor Queue. The front panel cos level is indirectly represented by the flow control mask value. This API is valid for XCore queuing devices. port parameter should have BCM_GPORT_INVALID value. The configuration is then applicable across the entire device. This API should be invoked after fabric ports and internal ports are created and their mapping to switch ports is established.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portfabric gport
[in]int_priinternal priority on fabric device
[out]flow_control_mask(for "_set") corresponding switch port flow control mask
(for "_get") corresponding switch port flow control mask

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_get()

int bcm_cosq_gport_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_gport_t *  physical_port,
int *  num_cos_levels,
uint32 *  flags 
)

Allocate/Retrieve unicast queue group and scheduler queue group configuration.

These APIs are used to allocate/retrieve unicast or multicast queue group or a scheduler queue group configuration. Scheduler queue groups are used to implement H-QoS. The set of CoS queues are uniquely identified with a GPORT ID, which represents the base CoS queue in the set. The GPORT ID is allocated from the next available queue in group of queues for the port or specified by the input when the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_ID flag is set. But the flag BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_ID is only supported for a few devices. BCM_GPORT_TYPE_UCAST_QUEUE_GROUP, BCM_GPORT_TYPE_MCAST_QUEUE_GROUP, or BCM_GPORT_TYPE_SCHEDULER type of GPORT can be added for hierarchical queuing (see also, bcm_cosq_gport_attach API). Depending on the functionality physical_port parameter can have one of the following values

  • unicast queue group => BCM_GPORT_MODPORT_SET()
  • multicast queue group => BCM_GPORT_MODPORT_SET()
  • scheduler queue group => BCM_GPORT_NULL When allocating a queue group the req_gport parameter direction depends on the flags. If BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_ID is specified the input direction is valid. Depending on the functionality the following macros can be used to create the req_gport.
  • unicast queue group => BCM_GPORT_UCAST_QUEUE_GROUP_SET()
  • multicast queue group => BCM_GPORT_MCAST_QUEUE_GROUP_SET()
  • scheduler queue group => BCM_GPORT_SCHEDULER_SET() req_gport parameter is always updated and should be subsequently used by the user. When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_ID flag is set, the value provided in the gport parameter is used as the GPORT ID, otherwise a unique GPORT ID will be allocated and returned. The feature using BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_ID to allocate a queue group is only supported for a few devices. For some devices that may not have the ability to shape every port or queue, the application can control whether the gport must be allocated from a shapeable or non-shapeable area. This can be done by specifying the flags BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_SHAPING or BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITHOUT_SHAPING, respectively. If neither flag is specified, the API will allocate a gport without paying any attention to whether it would be possible to configure a shaper on such port later. When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_OVERLAY flag is set, it allows overlay of queues that were previously allocated. When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_SUBSCRIBER flag is set, scheduling for the queue group will be done locally and will not involve the central arbiter. A local gport should be added only for ports which are local to that device. When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_MULTIPATH flag is set, a multipath shaper gport is created. Scheduler nodes on the same level could be added to the multipath shaper gport. The aggregated traffic from all nodes is shaped by the multipath shaper. The shaping rate of multipath shaper is controlled by calling bcm_cosq_gport_bandwidth_set API with the multipath shaper gport When the config.bcm variable "fabric_egress_setup=0" is set, FIFO-level egress support becomes available. The BCM_COSQ_GPORT_EGRESS_GROUP flag is used to enable egress group support. Egress Group gports are similar to egress child gports in all other aspects. The egress group gport connects a number of FIFOs to a subport and allows access at the FIFO-level. Multiple egress groups can be connected to the same subport up to sixteen FIFOs. In the case of egress gports, the num_cos_levels field is used to indicate the number of FIFOs to be associated with that egress gport. When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_DESTMOD_UCAST_QUEUE_GROUP flag is set, a set of virtual queue group (DMVOQ) is allocated. On BCM5645X chips, When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_DESTMOD_UCAST_QUEUE_GROUP flag is used with the combination of BCM_COSQ_GPORT_WITH_ID, the value provided in gport parameters is used as the GPORT_ID. But scheduling mode need to programmed again as per the scheduling hierarchy. API bcm_cosq_port_sched_set() can be used to set the scheduling mode to be Strict/WRR. When the BCM_COSQ_GPORT_VLAN_UCAST_QUEUE_GROUP flag is set, a queue to support service based queuing is allocated When a parent node is created by using bcm_cosq_gport_add API call by passing num_cos_levels = -1 then that node can have any number of child nodes. On the chips BCM5686x/BCM5685x/BCM56750/BCM56830/BCM5664x/BCM5604x/BCM5634x/BCM5654x, default schedule hierarchies are set up at SDK initialization. Default schedule hierarchy elements cannot be managed except using non-gport APIs to configure COSQs at port level. The first call to the API bcm_cosq_gport_add will destroy the default schedule hierarchies for all of ports and traffic will not flow on those ports until new schedule hierarchies for those ports are built. On the chips BCM56960 and BCM56870 API bcm_cosq_gport_add return BCM_E_PARAM because of fixed hierarchy. Gport tree is created during init. On the chips BCM56960 and BCM56870 because of fixed hierarchy scheduler the scope of COSQ GPORT is not global but it is local to per unit. So we should not modify the MODID dynamically. Some device configuration support multiple queue groups on a physical port.

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_mapping_get()

int bcm_cosq_gport_mapping_get ( int  unit,
bcm_port_t  ing_port,
bcm_cos_t  int_pri,
uint32  flags,
bcm_gport_t *  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t *  cosq 
)

Get or set the mapping from internal priority to CoS queue.

Configure or retrieve the mapping from the internal priority value to Cos Queue. The internal priority is usually initialized from the packet priority. For tagged packets the priority is extracted from the PRI field of the tag. For untagged packets, the priority is specified using the API bcm_port_untagged_priority_set . On some devices, the mapping tables may be shared among several ports, so setting one port's mappings may affect other ports'. On some devices, packets directed to the CPU interface port may have their priority assigned independent of this setting. For more information see bcm_switch_control_set . They can be used only on chips which support ETS(Enhanced Transmission Selection) feature regardless of that the ETS mode is enabled. If the gport value passed is -1 in set api then it is ignored. Mapping can be set by passing any of destination queue's gport or cosq, Get API would always return gport corresponding to the queue on source port. Set/get values could be different in such a case.

Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]ing_portIngress device or logical port or GPORT ID
[in]int_pri
[in]flagsCan be one of following BCM_COSQ_GPORT_UCAST_QUEUE_GROUP, BCM_COSQ_GPORT_DESTMOD_UCAST_QUEUE_GROUP, BCM_COSQ_GPORT_MCAST_QUEUE_GROUP
[out]gport(IN/OUT) GPORT ID for a queue group
[out]cosq(IN/OUT) CoS queue to which to map the chosen priority
Return values
BCM_E_NONE
BCM_E_PARAM
BCM_E_XXX

These APIs are used to manage members of multipath shaper. Member gports could be added to or deleted from the specified multipath shaper. multipath_get is used to get the current membership of the multipath shaper. User passes in the array pointer and the array size, API fills the array and return the number of valid entry in the array.

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_queue_attach()

int bcm_cosq_gport_queue_attach ( int  unit,
uint32  flags,
bcm_gport_t  ingress_queue,
bcm_cos_t  ingress_int_pri,
bcm_gport_t  egress_queue,
bcm_cos_t  egress_int_pri,
int *  attach_id 
)

When the config.bcm variable "fabric_egress_setup=0" is set, FIFO-level egress support becomes available. Queue attach is used to associate an ingress queue with an egress FIFO allocated when creating an egress group (see also bcm_cosq_gport_add API). By default, the first queue is associated with the first FIFO, which is assigned EF traffic and the second queue is associated with the second FIFO and receives NON-EF traffic. The subsequent two queues receive Multicast EF and Non-Ef traffic. With this feature enabled, individual queues can be directed to specific FIFOs. Multicast is a special case as the flow control domain for Multicast traffic is pre-allocated. Therefore, instead of ingress priority, use BCM_COS_MULTICAST_EF to associate a specific queue with multicast EF traffic and BCM_COS_MULTICAST_NON_EF to associate the rest of multicast traffic to another queue. When passing queue attach get an ingress_queue, cos level, and attach_id, the get routine will return the egress group number and corresponding FIFO number paired with the ingress queue. To detach a FIFO from an ingress queue and restore the default FIFO, pass the ingress queue, cos level, and attach_id into queue detach.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]flagsBCM_COSQ_GPORT_QUEUE_ATTACH_WITH_ID
[in]ingress_queueIngress queue Group gport
[in]ingress_int_priCoS priority for unicast or BCM_COS_MULTICAST_EF or BCM_COS_MULTICAST_NON_EF
[in]egress_queue(IN/OUT) Egress Group gport
[in]egress_int_pri(IN/OUT) FIFO index to associate to Ingress Queue
[in,out]attach_id(IN/OUT) Attach ID value connecting queue/FIFO pairing

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_rate_class_create()

create a rate class with the specified attributes.

This function is used to create a rate class. some rate class attributes are set to defaults and other attributes are set according to information in create_info structure. This function should be called for every rate class in use. after the rate class is created, user can overrun the rate class attributes using designated APIs.

attributes specific rate class attributes. see COSQ_RATE_CLASS_CREATE_ATTR_XXX

BCM_COSQ_RATE_CLASS_CREATE_ATTR_OCB_ONLY rate class to be used on OCB only.
BCM_COSQ_RATE_CLASS_CREATE_ATTR_MULTICAST rate class for FMQs (Fabric Multicast Queues).

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_reattach()

int bcm_cosq_gport_reattach ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  sched_port,
bcm_gport_t  input_port,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq 
)

Reattach the output of a GPORT to the input of a scheduler GPORT.

This API can be used to reattach the output of a GPORT to the input of a scheduler GPORT to form a queuing hierarchy. The connect is done at the specified CoS queue of the Scheduler GPORT. A cosq value of -1 will attach the input GPORT to the first unused CoS queue of the Scheduler GPORT (going from higher to lower CoS queue priority).

Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]sched_portScheduler GPORT ID
[in]input_portGPORT ID that will attach to scheduler gport
[in]cosqCoS queue to attach to

Get/set queue report thresholds. The maximum number of 4 thresholds is supported per queue. They apply to the dynamical bandwidth allocation of EPON.

threshold1 Queue report threshold1.
threshold2 Queue report threshold2.
threshold3 Queue report threshold3.

(for "_get") Queue report thresholds

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_sched_get()

int bcm_cosq_gport_sched_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
int *  mode,
int *  weight 
)

Configure/retrieve scheduling policy.

Configure/Retrieve scheduling modes. Set or Get the Class of Service policy and weight for the specified GPORT. The gport parameter can be a physical port, in which case the CoS queue specified by the cosq parameter is one of the default CoS queues assigned to the port during initialization. Alternatively, the gport parameter can be a scheduler GPORT that was dynamically added with bcm_cosq_gport_add or bcm_cosq_fabric_distribution_add . In this case, the GPORT ID represents the base CoS queue and the cosq parameter identifies the specific CoS queue as an offset from the base. It is not recommanded to use gport for queue (L2 gport) as gport parameter (on 5644X and 5645X it is not supported). In Tomahawk series, cos queue can be inspected from scheduler/queue GPORT so "cosq" from API is silently ignored. Note: In ETS(Enhanced Transmission Selection) mode, given gport is port's gport and cosq == -1, BCM_E_PARAM will be returned. In Non-ETS mode, cosq == -1 will configure all cosq's. XCore device Mode options are listed in the table below. BCM_SBX_COSQ_GPORT_table

BCM XCore CoSQ GPORT Modes
Mode Description
BCM_COSQ_SP Strict Priority. weight parameter represents the weight associated with a flow.
BCM_COSQ_EF Expedited Forwarding.
BCM_COSQ_AF Assured Forwarding.
BCM_COSQ_SP_GLOBAL Global Strict Priority. weight parameter represents the priority.
BCM_COSQ_BE Best Effort.
BCM_COSQ_WFQ Weighted Fair Queuing. weight parameter represents the weight associated with a flow.
BCM_COSQ_SP[0-10] Global Strict Priority. BCM_COSQ_SP10 priority > BCM_COSQ_SP9 priority > ... > BCM_COSQ_SP0 priority.
BCM_COSQ_GSP[0-10] Global Strict Priority. BCM_COSQ_GSP10 priority > BCM_COSQ_GSP9 priority > ... > BCM_COSQ_GSP0 priority.
COSQ_DELAY_TOLERANCE_NORMAL Delay tolerance is normal
COSQ_DELAY_TOLERANCE_LOW_DELAY Delay tolerance is low delay
COSQ_DELAY_TOLERANCE_[02-07] Flexible delay tolerance level. Mainly needed for interfaces with rates higher than 10G (such as Interlaken)
COSQ_DELAY_TOLERANCE_[08-23] Flexible delay tolerance level.
COSQ_DELAY_TOLERANCE_SLOW_LEVELS Number of slow threshold levels.
BCM_COSQ_PON_DROPDOWN EPON DBA Dropdown value

Non-XCore device Mode options are listed in the table below. See table BCM_COSQ_COMBO for weight options. For modes which use weights, the weights may range between BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_MIN and the value of weight_max returned by bcm_cosq_sched_weight_max_get for the mode. If weight_max = BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_UNLIMITED, then any positive weight is acceptable. For modes which use weights, BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_STRICT may be supplied for the weight, indicating these queues should behave as in strict priority mode. The chips BCM5644x/BCM5645x does not support the scheduling modes BCM_COSQ_WEIGHTED_FAIR_QUEUING and BCM_COSQ_BOUNDED_DELAY.

BCM CoSQ Modes
Mode Description
BCM_COSQ_STRICT Highest priority packets always egress first. In this mode weight is ignored.
BCM_COSQ_ROUND_ROBIN Scheduling between queues uses a simple round robin algorithm. In this mode weight is ignored.
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHTED_ROUND_ROBIN Scheduling between queues uses a weighted round robin algorithm.
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHTED_FAIR_QUEUING Scheduling between queues uses a weighted fair queuing algorithm. Requires use of bcm_cosq_gport_bandwidth_set for full configuration.
BCM_COSQ_BOUNDED_DELAY Scheduling between queues uses a weighted round robin algorithm with bounded time delay.
BCM_COSQ_DEFICIT_ROUND_ROBIN Scheduling between queues uses a deficit round robin algorithm.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]gportGPORT ID for a queue group
[in]cosqCoS Queue
[out]mode(for "_set") scheduling mode
(for "_get") scheduling mode. see table BCM_SBX_COSQ_GPORT_table
[out]weight(for "_set") weight. This is applicable for some scheduling modes
(for "_get") weight. This is applicable for some scheduling modes

int bcm_cosq_gport_threshold_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
bcm_cosq_threshold_t *  threshold 
)

Configuring/retrieving Ingress / egress Thresholds for Flow control and Admission Control.

Configuring/retrieving Ingress / egress Thresholds for Flow control and Admission Control

// flow control / admission settings
typedef struct bcm_cosq_threshold_s {
uint32 flags; // BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_* flag values
bcm_color_t dp; // drop precedence. relevant for BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_PER_DP flag value
bcm_cosq_threshold_type_t type; // threshold type
int value; // threshold value for drop/flow control
int tc; // traffic class for which the thresholds are to be configured
int vsq_category; // VSQ category for which the thresholds are to be configured
uint32 valid; // a bitmap representing enabled fields in the struct.
int priority; // priority
} bcm_cosq_threshold_t;

BCM COSQ GPORT Threshold configuration
Parameter Description
flags BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_* flag values. see BCM_COSQ_GPORT_THRESHOLD_flags
dp drop precedence. relevant for BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_PER_DP flag value
type threshold type. see BCM_COSQ_GPORT_THRESHOLD_types
value threshold value for drop/flow control

Threshold flags
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_PER_DP dp field meaningful
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_INGRESS device level ingress thresholds
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_EGRESS device level egress thresholds
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_UNICAST device level unicast thresholds
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_MULTICAST device level multicast thresholds
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_SET threshold for assert condition (where applicable)
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_CLEAR threshold for de-assert (where applicable)
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_NOT_COMMIT to aid in template management
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_FLOW_CONTROL flow control
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_DROP Admission Control
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_MULTICAST_SP0 Multicast Service-Pool 0
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_MULTICAST_SP1 Multicast Service-Pool 1
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_COLOR_SYSTEM_RED Set Color System red format. Color parameter will present system red size value.
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_RANGE_0 Set Range 0 threshold, where threshold value indicates the max size of the specific range
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_RANGE_1 Set Range 1 threshold, where threshold value indicates the max size of the specific range
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_RANGE_2 Set Range 2 threshold, where threshold value indicates the max size of the specific range
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_RANGE_3 Set Range 3 threshold, where threshold value indicates the max size of the specific range
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_OCB On-Chip buffer
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_RCI Set threshold value for RCI
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_ETH_PORT_LLFC Set LLFC threshold value for Ethernet port
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_ETH_PORT_PFC Set PFC threshold value for Ethernet port
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_POOL0 Set threshold value for shared Pool 0 resource
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_POOL1 Set threshold value for shared Pool 1 resource
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_QSIZE_RECOVERY Queue size recovery threshold settings
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_HEADROOM Set threshold value for sram headroom resource

Threshold types
bcmCosqThresholdBytes consumed bytes. Egress Drop threshold, Unicast, multicast, dp (multicast) at port and device level. Egress Flow control threshold, unicast, multicast, port, channel and device level.
bcmCosqThresholdPacketDescriptors consumed packet descriptors. Egress drop threshold, unicast, multicast, dp (multicast) at port level. Egress Flow control threshold, unicast, multicast device level.
bcmCosqThresholdPackets consumed packets. Egress Drop threshold, Unicast, multicast, dp(multicast) at device level. Egress Flow control threshold, multicast at device level.
bcmCosqThresholdDataBuffers consumed data buffers. Egress Drop threshold, multicast, dp at device level Egress Flow control threshold, unicast, multicast at device level.
bcmCosqThresholdAvailablePacketDescriptors available Packet Descriptors. Egress Drop threshold, Unicast, multicast, dp (multicast) at port and device level.
bcmCosqThresholdAvailableDataBuffers available data buffers. Egress Drop threshold, multicast, dp at device level.
bcmCosqThresholdBufferDescriptorBuffers consumed Buffer descriptor Buffers. Ingress Drop threshold, DP at device level. Ingress Flow control threshold at device level.
bcmCosqThresholdBufferDescriptors consumed buffer descriptors. Ingress Drop threshold, DP at device level.
bcmCosqThresholdDbuffs consumed Dbuffs. Ingress Drop threshold, DP, unicast at device level. Ingress flow control threshold, unicast, multicast at device level.
bcmCosqThresholdFullDbuffs consumed Full Dbuffs. Ingress Drop threshold, DP, multicast at device level.
bcmCosqThresholdMiniDbuffs consumed mini Dbuffs. Ingress Drop threshold, DP, multicast at device level.
bcmCosqThresholdDynamicWeight Dynamic scheduling threshold.
bcmCosqThresholdPacketDescriptorsMin Fair Adaptive Thresholds support for bcmCosqThresholdPacketDescriptors.
bcmCosqThresholdPacketDescriptorsMax Fair Adaptive Thresholds support for bcmCosqThresholdPacketDescriptors.
bcmCosqThresholdPacketDescriptorsAlpha Fair Adaptive Thresholds support for bcmCosqThresholdPacketDescriptors.
bcmCosqThresholdDataBuffersMin Fair Adaptive Thresholds support for bcmCosqThresholdDataBuffers.
bcmCosqThresholdDataBuffersMax Fair Adaptive Thresholds support for bcmCosqThresholdDataBuffers.
bcmCosqThresholdDataBuffersAlpha Fair Adaptive Thresholds support for bcmCosqThresholdDataBuffers.
bcmCosqThresholdOcbDbuffs consumed OCB Dbuffs. Ingress Drop threshold, DP, at device level.
bcmCosqThresholdPacketDescriptorBuffers consumed PDBs. Ingress Drop threshold, DP, at device level.
bcmCosqThresholdBundleDescriptorBuffers consumed Bundle Descriptor Buffers. Ingress Drop threshold, DP, at device level.
bcmCosqThresholdDataBuffersAlpha1 set an additional alpha (Alpha1) for fair adaptive supporting thresholds.

Threshold Valid Bitmamp
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_VALID_DP dp field should be be used
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_VALID_VALUE value field should be be used
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_VALID_TC tc field should be be used
BCM_COSQ_THRESHOLD_VALID_VSQ_CATEGORY vsq category field should be be used
Parameters
[in]unit[IN] BCM device number
[in]gport[IN] GPORT ID for a queue group (unicast/multicast egress queue group)
[in]cosq[IN] Cos Queue
[in,out]threshold[IN] (for "_set") threshold configuration
[INOUT] (for "_get") threshold configuration

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_vsq_create()

int bcm_cosq_gport_vsq_create ( int  unit,
bcm_cosq_vsq_info_t *  vsq_info,
bcm_gport_t *  vsq_gport 
)

Create the VSQ.

Allocate vsq group by giving vsq info settings.

flag values for VSQ creation
BCM_COSQ_VSQ_GL create 1 global VSQ
BCM_COSQ_VSQ_CT create according to Category
BCM_COSQ_VSQ_CTTC create according to Category Traffic-Class
BCM_COSQ_VSQ_CTCC create according to Category Connection-Class
BCM_COSQ_VSQ_PP create according to ST-VSQ-Pointer, arrived from the field processor or external PP
BCM_COSQ_VSQ_LLFC create according to Source Network Port
BCM_COSQ_VSQ_PFC create according to Packet Priority

VSQ info settings
Parameter Description
flags flags for vsq info. see table BCM_COSQ_VSQ_INFO_flags
ct_id Category ID. Relevant when flag is CT/CTTC/CTCC.
cc_id Connection Class ID. Relevant when flag is CTCC.
src_port Source Physical port ID. The network interface ID that the packet arrived from. Relevant when flag is LLFC, PFC.
flow_control_pri The PFC level to be generated when the source-port*TC VSQ is over subscribed. Relevant when flag is PFC.
pp_vsq_id The ID of the VSQ, in the PP space. Relevant when flag PP is set. In this case, the user specifies the ST-VSQ-Pointer in the range 0-255 from the FP/PP that needs to be mapped to the VSQ.
core_id The core ID of the VSQ.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]vsq_info[IN] VSQ info settings
[out]vsq_gport[INOUT] gport referencing vsq

◆ bcm_cosq_gport_vsq_delete()

BCM_COSQ_GPORT_VSQ_CORE_ID_GET(_gport) Get core id

[in]hdrm_poolHeadroom pool id for which pool limit needs to be set.
[in]num_lossless_classMax. number of lossless classes expected to use the headroom pool in a given time.
[in]arr_sizeArray size of packet distribution. (Max value: 3)
[in]pkt_dist_arrayArray of packet distribution structure Sum of percentages of different packet sizes in input array should equal 100.

◆ bcm_cosq_mapping_get()

int bcm_cosq_mapping_get ( int  unit,
bcm_cos_t  priority,
bcm_cos_queue_t *  cosq 
)

Get or set the mapping from internal priority to CoS queue.

Configure or retrieve the mapping from the internal priority value to Cos Queue. The internal priority is usually initialized from the packet priority. For tagged packets the priority is extracted from the PRI field of the tag. For untagged packets, the priority is specified using the API bcm_port_untagged_priority_set . On some devices, the mapping tables may be shared among several ports, so setting one port's mappings may affect other ports'. On some devices, packets directed to the CPU interface port may have their priority assigned independent of this setting. For more information see bcm_switch_control_set . On some devices, a port value of -1 or gport type for system configuration will configure all ports. Some devices support Enhanced Transmission Selection (ETS) which requires to use GPORT ID for the port argument. When the ETS mode is enabled, they configure and retrive the mapping from the internal priority to the offset (which is equal to the value of cosq) of the unicast queues and multicast queues attached to the egress port. Most devices have 8 internal priorities (0 to 7).

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]priorityinternal priority to map
[out]cosqCos queue to which to map the chosen priority
Return values
BCM_E_NONE
BCM_E_PARAMInvalid priority, or device not configured for the number of CoS queues specified.
BCM_E_XXX

// integrated cosq index for cosq APIs
typedef struct bcm_cosq_object_id_s {
bcm_gport_t port; // gport

◆ bcm_cosq_pfc_class_config_profile_get()

int bcm_cosq_pfc_class_config_profile_get ( int  unit,
int  profile_id,
int  max_count,
bcm_cosq_pfc_class_map_config_t *  config_array,
int *  count 
)

Get / set PFC class configurations (e.g. PFC priority to COSQ mapping) for a profile.

Get / set PFC class configurations for a profile including PFC priority to COSQ mapping and PFC group optimization. For _set function, configurations for all PFC priorities are required, i.e. count should be equal to 8. config_array[i] stores the configuration for PFC priority i implicitly. Not all PFC priories need to be enabled. PFC priority to COS mapping is a many-to-many mapping. PFC profile cannot modified while there is traffic on any ports using the profile.

Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]profile_idPFC Class Profile Id.
[in]max_count
[out]config_array(for "_set") Array of PFC class configuration
(for "_get") Array of PFC class configuration
[out]count(for "_set") Number of PFC class configurations in config_array
(for "_get") Number of configurations returned

◆ bcm_cosq_pfc_class_mapping_get()

int bcm_cosq_pfc_class_mapping_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  port,
int  array_max,
bcm_cosq_pfc_class_mapping_t *  mapping_array,
int *  array_count 
)

Get / set mapping of PFC class to COSQs and / or scheduling nodes for a port.

Get or set mapping between PFC class and COSQs and / or scheduling nodes for a port. Multiple mappings for a list of PFC class can be set at one time. Each PFC class can be mapped to multiple COSQs and / or scheduling nodes identified by gport id. Not all PFC classes are needed. User only set a group of PFC classes that system has to respond to. For \sc _get\ec, the number of PFC class mappings associated with the port is returned by \sc array_count\ec. PFC class and associated COSq priority or scheduling node's gport ID are returned respectively by class and gport_list in \sc mapping_array\ec. gport_list is ended by \sc BCM_GPORT_INVALID\ec, when retrieved gports does not full fill the list. If array_max<=0 and \sc mapping_array==NULL\ec, only array_count is returned.

#define BCM_COSQ_PFC_GPORT_COUNT 26
// PFC class to COSq / scheduling node mapping structure.
typedef struct bcm_cosq_pfc_class_mapping_s {
int class_id; // PFC class.
bcm_gport_t gport_list[BCM_COSQ_PFC_GPORT_COUNT]; // mapped COSqs, -1 for no mapping.
} bcm_cosq_pfc_class_mapping_t;
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portLogical port number
[in]array_max(for "_get") Number of mappings allocated in mapping_array
[out]mapping_array(for "_set") Array of PFC class mappings
(for "_get") Array of PFC class mappings
[out]array_count(for "_set") Number of mappings in mapping_array
(for "_get") Number of mappings returned

◆ bcm_cosq_pfc_config_get()

int bcm_cosq_pfc_config_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
uint32  flags,
bcm_cosq_pfc_config_t *  config 
)

Configure Priority-Based Flow Control (PFC).

PFC configuration is listed in the following tables. BCM_COSQ_PFC_CONFIG_table

BCM CoSQ PFC Configuration
Parameter Description
xoff_threshold Assert backpressure when number of buffers used is at or above this threshold
xon_threshold Remove backpressure when number of buffers used drops below this threshold
xoff_fadt_threshold Assert backpressure when number of resources used is at or above this FADT threshold
xon_fadt_offset Remove backpressure when number of resources used drops below FADT threshold defined by xoff_fadt_threshold - fadt_offset
xoff_threshold_bd Assert backpressure when number of buffer descriptors used is at or above this threshold
xon_threshold_bd Remove backpressure when number of buffer descriptors used drops below this threshold
drop_threshold Drop packets when number of buffers used hit this threshold
reserved_buffers Number of buffers reserved for the specified priority
lossless lossless PFC enable for the specified priority

Configure the priority-based flow control (PFC) features. When gport is set to BCM_GPORT_INVALID, the API configs the thresholds for the priority specified by the cosq parameter. For (source port, priority) based flow control scheme, the gport specifies the source port. It is possible that devices support both per priority threshold and (source port, priority) threshold at the same time. Typical settings for the thresholds are drop_threshold >= xoff_threshold >= xon_threshold, When the buffers used for a priority hit or go above the xoff_threshold, backpressure is asserted, if the buffers used are at drop_threshld, all incoming packets will be dropped. when the buffers used for the priority drops below the xon_threshold, backpressure is removed. drop_threshold could be disabled when set to 0. For a particular device, it is possible only some config parameters applies, unused configs will be ignored by SDK.

#define BCM_COSQ_PFC_BYTES // threshold in bytes
#define BCM_COSQ_PFC_OCB // threshold for OCB (SRAM) resources
#define BCM_COSQ_PFC_PACKET_DESC // threshold in packet descriptors
#define BCM_COSQ_PFC_BUFFERS // threshold in buffers
#define BCM_COSQ_PFC_USE_FADT_PARAMS // Use FADT parameters
Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]gportSource port for Source port/Priority based flow control scheme, pass in BCM_GPORT_INVALID for Priority only based flow control scheme.
[in]cosqPacket priority
[in]flagsSpecifies configuration. Valid flags: BCM_COSQ_GPORT_PFC_CONFIG_WITH_ID
[out]configPFC configurations. see table BCM_COSQ_PFC_CONFIG_table .

◆ bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_config_get()

int bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_config_get ( int  unit,
int  priority,
bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_config_t *  config 
)

Set/Get config for the given priority for the PFC Deadlock feature.

Configure PFC deadlock config structure for a given priority. The config include "detection_timer" and "recovery_timer". detection_timer(IN/OUT) - indicates the time for Hardware to monitor a specific Cos queue of a Port. recovery_timer(IN/OUT) - indicates the time for Software to retain the Port's queue in Recovery state

  1. Detection: Setup Detection timer. Hardware monitors enabled Port's queues (for configured priority). If enabled Queues remain in XOFF state beyond the deadlock_timer, Hardware declares Deadlock.

When Deadlock is detected, Packets can be transmitted ignoring PFC congestion status (Default), or can be configured to be discarded during the deadlockrecovery period using switch control bcmSwitchPFCDeadlockRecoveryAction).

  1. Recovery: Software keeps polling for the Deadlock status. When Deadlock is set, Software sets the Action(Ignore PFC Status or Packet discard)
  2. Software runs a recovery timer configured by the user/application. On expiry of recovery timer, Sw will have to remove/reset the action. Legacy device will support only wired cos. For the new devices will supports wired, wireless Legacy devices support only wired cos. The newer devices (Like Helix-5) supports wired, wireless and transit cos. To map priority between different cos, it needs to be encoded with different cos types, an example of which is shown below. a map the priority to wired cos Priority = priority | BCM_COSQ_PFC_DEADLOCK_WIRED_COS; b. To map the priority to wireless cos Priority = priority | BCM_COSQ_PFC_DEADLOCK_WIRELESS_COS; c. To map the priority to transit cos Priority = priority | BCM_COSQ_PFC_DEADLOCK_TRANSIT_COS;
    typedef struct bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_config_s {
    uint32 detection_timer; // PFC Deadlock Detection Timer.
    uint32 recovery_timer; // PFC Deadlock Recovery Timer.
    } bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_config_t;
Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]priorityPriority for the given config
[out]config(IN/OUT) Config struture for given priority

◆ bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_config_set()

◆ bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_control_get()

int bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_control_get ( int  unit,
bcm_port_t  port,
int  pfc_priority,
bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_control_t  type,
int *  arg 
)

Set / Get config for the given (PFC priority, port) for the PFC Deadlock feature.

Configure PFC deadlock settings for a given (port, PFC priority).

  1. Detection: Setup Detection timer. Hardware monitors enabled Port's PFC priority. If enabled PFC priority remain in XOFF state beyond the deadlock_timer, Hardware declares Deadlock.

When Deadlock is detected, Packets can be transmitted ignoring PFC congestion status (Default), or can be configured to be discarded during the deadlockrecovery period using switch control bcmSwitchPFCDeadlockRecoveryAction).

  1. Recovery: Software keeps polling for the Deadlock status. When Deadlock is set, Software sets the Action(Ignore PFC Status or Packet discard)
  2. Software runs a recovery timer configured by the user/application. On expiry of recovery timer, Sw will have to remove/reset the action.
    PFC deadlock control type values
    Value Description Arg value
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockDetectionAndRecoveryEnable Enable/disable PFC deadlock detection and recovery per-port per-PFC priority. 0: disable, 1: enable.
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockRecoveryOccurences accumulated time a port stays in pfc deadlock state per-PFC priority [in milliseconds]. for "_set" function, only 0 is valid
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockDetectionTimer PFC deadlock Hardware timer in milliseconds Valid values are in range of [0, 15 * timer_granularity] with a step of timer_granularity
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockRecoveryTimer Software recovery timer in multiples of 100 milliseconds. Values greater than 0
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockTimerGranularity timer granularity see PFC_DEADLOCK_TIMER_table for valid values
    PFC deadlock timer values
    Value Description
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockTimerInterval1MiliSecond 1ms timer granularity
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockTimerInterval10MiliSecond 10ms timer granularity
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockTimerInterval100MiliSecond 100ms timer granularity
Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]portDevice or logical port number
[in]pfc_priorityPFC Priority
[in]typePFC deadlock control type (see PFC_DEADLOCK_CONTROL_TYPE_table)
[out]arg(IN/OUT) Argument whose meaning is dependent on type

    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockDetectionAndRecoveryEnable Enable/disable PFC deadlock detection and recovery per-port per-PFC priority. 0: disable, 1: enable.
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockRecoveryOccurences accumulated time a port stays in pfc deadlock state per-PFC priority [in milliseconds]. for "_set" function, only 0 is valid
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockDetectionTimer PFC deadlock Hardware timer in milliseconds Valid values are in range of [0, 15 * timer_granularity] with a step of timer_granularity
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockRecoveryTimer Software recovery timer in multiples of 100 milliseconds. Values greater than 0
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockTimerGranularity timer granularity see PFC_DEADLOCK_TIMER_table for valid values
    PFC deadlock timer values
    Value Description
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockTimerInterval1MiliSecond 1ms timer granularity
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockTimerInterval10MiliSecond 10ms timer granularity
    bcmCosqPFCDeadlockTimerInterval100MiliSecond 100ms timer granularity
Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]portDevice or logical port number
[in]pfc_priorityPFC Priority
[in]typePFC deadlock control type (see PFC_DEADLOCK_CONTROL_TYPE_table)
[in]arg(IN/OUT) Argument whose meaning is dependent on type

◆ bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_info_get()

int bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_info_get ( int  unit,
int  priority,
bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_info_t *  pfc_deadlock_info 
)

Get bitmap of Enabled(Admin) and Current Deadlock ports status.

Get bitmap of Enabled(Admin) and Current Deadlock ports status for a given priority in PFC deadlock feature. In new devices priority should have mapped to either wired, wireless and transit cos. In newer devices (Like Helix-5) priority would have been mapped to either wired, wireless and transit cos. To get the bitmap of Enabled(Admin) and Current Deadlock status for a given priority on different cos (Wired, Wireless, transit), priority needs to be encoded, example of this is as shown below. a. For Wired cos. Priority = priority | BCM_COSQ_PFC_DEADLOCK_WIRED_COS; b. For wireless cos. Priority = priority | BCM_COSQ_PFC_DEADLOCK_WIRELESS_COS; c. For Transit cos. Priority = priority | BCM_COSQ_PFC_DEADLOCK_TRANSIT_COS; By default without encoding it will get port bit maps for priority mapped to wired cos.

typedef struct bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_info_s {
bcm_pbmp_t enabled_pbmp; // Bitmap of ports enabled for a given priority.
bcm_pbmp_t deadlock_pbmp; // Bitmap of ports currently in deadlock status for a given priority.
} bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_info_t;
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]priorityPriority for the given config
[out]pfc_deadlock_infoInfo struture for given priority

◆ bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_recovery_exit()

int bcm_cosq_pfc_deadlock_recovery_exit ( int  unit,
bcm_port_t  port,
bcm_cos_t  cosq 
)

Start/Exit PFC Deadlock recovery process.

Start or Exit the pfc deadlock recovery, soc property PFC_DEADLOCK_SEQ_CONTROL should be configured in configuration file to make these API work. Start pfc deadlock recovery will disable pfc deadlock detect and make the port ignore PFC_XOFF state. Exit pfc deadlock recovery will enable pfc deadlock detect if it is already enabled and make the port response PFC_XOFF state.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portport number
[in]cosq

◆ bcm_cosq_port_bandwidth_get()

int bcm_cosq_port_bandwidth_get ( int  unit,
bcm_port_t  port,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
uint32 *  kbits_sec_min,
uint32 *  kbits_sec_max,
uint32 *  flags 
)

Configure a port's bandwidth distribution among CoS queues.

On some devices, the bandwidth allocated to each CoS queue may be configured. The maximum bandwidth setting is applicable to any mode on these devices. However, for non-XCore (tm) and non-XGS devices, the minimum bandwidth settings and the preference flags are only valid when the WEIGHTED_FAIR_QUEUING mode is selected. The order of the calls bcm_cosq_port_bandwidth_set and bcm_cosq_port_sched_set is not important. A port value of -1 or gport type for system configuration will configure all ports, and a cosq value of -1 will configure all cosq's. The supplied bandwidth values may be rounded up to the nearest value supported by the HW. The available flags for bandwidth response tuning are BCM_COSQ_BW_f

Port Bandwidth Flags
Flag Description
BCM_COSQ_BW_EAV_MODE Enable EAV mode
BCM_COSQ_BW_LLFC Link level flow control
BCM_COSQ_BW_PACKET_MODE The bandwidth specified is in packets per second instead of kbits per second
BCM_COSQ_BW_NOT_COMMIT Set rate to SW DB only, commit to HW is done when calling the API with the same GPort type and without NOT_COMMIT flag
BCM_COSQ_BW_EAV_TAS_MODE Avoid burstiness when gate is opening or after queue is empty
BCM_COSQ_BW_TAS_TOKEN_FREEZE Freeze shaper token when gate is closed to avoid burstiness
BCM_COSQ_BW_ALT_CALC Use alternative building algorithm for bandwidth calculation

Bandwidth for the port is allocated until exhausted at any step in this algorithm.

Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]portDevice or logical port
[in]cosqCos Queue to configure
[out]kbits_sec_minMinimum bandwidth in kbits/sec.
[out]kbits_sec_maxMaximum bandwidth in kbits/sec.
[out]flagsBandwidth tuning parameters.

◆ bcm_cosq_port_mapping_get()

int bcm_cosq_port_mapping_get ( int  unit,
bcm_port_t  port,
bcm_cos_t  priority,
bcm_cos_queue_t *  cosq 
)

Get or set the mapping from internal priority to CoS queue.

Configure or retrieve the mapping from the internal priority value to Cos Queue. The internal priority is usually initialized from the packet priority. For tagged packets the priority is extracted from the PRI field of the tag. For untagged packets, the priority is specified using the API bcm_port_untagged_priority_set . On some devices, the mapping tables may be shared among several ports, so setting one port's mappings may affect other ports'. On some devices, packets directed to the CPU interface port may have their priority assigned independent of this setting. For more information see bcm_switch_control_set . On some devices, a port value of -1 or gport type for system configuration will configure all ports. Some devices support Enhanced Transmission Selection (ETS) which requires to use GPORT ID for the port argument. When the ETS mode is enabled, they configure and retrive the mapping from the internal priority to the offset (which is equal to the value of cosq) of the unicast queues and multicast queues attached to the egress port. Most devices have 8 internal priorities (0 to 7).

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portDevice or logical port or GPORT ID
[in]priorityinternal priority to map
[out]cosqCos queue to which to map the chosen priority
Return values
BCM_E_NONE
BCM_E_PARAMInvalid priority, or device not configured for the number of CoS queues specified.
BCM_E_XXX

◆ bcm_cosq_port_sched_config_get()

int bcm_cosq_port_sched_config_get ( int  unit,
bcm_pbmp_t  pbm,
int  weight_arr_size,
int *  weights,
int *  weight_arr_count,
int *  mode 
)

Get or set Class of Service policy, weights and delay.

Configure or retrieve the Class of Service policy, weights, and delay for a device or port. The mode options are listed in the table below. For modes which use weights, the weights may range between BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_MIN and the value of weight_max returned by bcm_cosq_sched_weight_max_get for the mode. If weight_max = BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_UNLIMITED, then any positive weight is acceptable. In BCM_COSQ_BOUNDED_DELAY mode, a negative value for an element of the weight array indicates that the weight and delay value for that Class of Service should remain unchanged, while the non-negative elements of the weight array are updated and assigned the given delay value. For modes which use weights, BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_STRICT may be supplied for some of the weights, indicating these queues should behave as in strict priority mode. Supported for chip BCM5698X. Note: In all devices supporting Enhanced Transmission Selection (ETS) hierarchical scheduling, bcm_cosq_sched_set and bcm_cosq_sched_get API is used to configure and retrieve the Class of Service policy, weights, and delay for CPU(CMIC) port only.

Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]pbmPort bit map of ports to configure
[in]weight_arr_sizeSize of the weights array
[out]weightsArray of relative weights indexed by CoS queue. The size of the array is specified in weight_arr_size
[out]weight_arr_countNumber of valid entries in the weights array
[out]modeScheduling mode, see table BCM_COSQ_table

int *  mode,
int  weights[BCM_COS_COUNT],
int *  delay 
)

Get or set Class of Service policy, weights and delay.

Configure or retrieve the Class of Service policy, weights, and delay for a device or port. The mode options are listed in the table below. For modes which use weights, the weights may range between BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_MIN and the value of weight_max returned by bcm_cosq_sched_weight_max_get for the mode. If weight_max = BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_UNLIMITED, then any positive weight is acceptable. In BCM_COSQ_BOUNDED_DELAY mode, a negative value for an element of the weight array indicates that the weight and delay value for that Class of Service should remain unchanged, while the non-negative elements of the weight array are updated and assigned the given delay value. For modes which use weights, BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_STRICT may be supplied for some of the weights, indicating these queues should behave as in strict priority mode. On the chips BCM5685x/BCM56750/BCM56830, the queues in strict priority mode must be in consecutive order. The chips BCM5644x/BCM5645x does not support the scheduling modes BCM_COSQ_WEIGHTED_FAIR_QUEUING and BCM_COSQ_BOUNDED_DELAY. Note: In all devices supporting Enhanced Transmission Selection (ETS) hierarchical scheduling, bcm_cosq_sched_set and bcm_cosq_sched_get API is used to configure and retrieve the Class of Service policy, weights, and delay for CPU(CMIC) port only.

BCM CoSQ Modes
Mode Description
BCM_COSQ_STRICT Highest priority packets always egress first. In this mode weight is ignored.
BCM_COSQ_ROUND_ROBIN Scheduling between queues uses a simple round robin algorithm. In this mode weight is ignored.
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHTED_ROUND_ROBIN Scheduling between queues uses a weighted round robin algorithm.
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHTED_FAIR_QUEUING Scheduling between queues uses a weighted fair queuing algorithm. Requires use of bcm_cosq_port_bandwidth_set for full configuration.
BCM_COSQ_BOUNDED_DELAY Scheduling between queues uses a weighted round robin algorithm with bounded time delay.
BCM_COSQ_DEFICIT_ROUND_ROBIN Scheduling between queues uses a deficit round robin algorithm.

BCM CoSQ Discrete Weight
Mode Description
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_DISCRETE_WEIGHT_LEVEL0 weight associated with level 0 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute.
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_DISCRETE_WEIGHT_LEVEL1 weight associated with level 1 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute.
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_DISCRETE_WEIGHT_LEVEL2 weight associated with level 2 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute.
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_DISCRETE_WEIGHT_LEVEL3 weight associated with level 3 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute.
Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]pbmPort bit map of ports to configure
[out]modeScheduling mode, see table BCM_COSQ_table
[out]weightsArray of relative weights indexed by CoS queue. Use depends on the selected mode. See BCM_COSQ_COMBO . Note: Be aware that despite of BCM_COS_COUNT is 8, it supports up to 10 weights arrays in BCM5696x devices if and only if bcm_num_cos=10 is configured.
[out]delayUsed only if scheduling algorithm is BCM_COSQ_BOUNDED_DELAY to indicate the maximum amount of time before returning to the highest priority CoS queue. This value is only used for non-negative elements of the weights array.

◆ bcm_cosq_priority_group_pfc_priority_mapping_profile_get()

int  profile_id,
int  array_max,
int *  pg_array,
int *  array_count 
)

Get / set mapping of PFC priority to Priority Group for a profile.

Get or set mappings between PFC Priority and Priority Group for a profile. Multiple mappings for a list of PFC Priorities can be set at one time. pg_array is indexed by PFC priority, i.e. pg_array[i] specifies the PG number that PFC priority i is mapped to and -1 means unmapped. PFC priorities to PG mapping is many-to-one mapping. Multiple PFC priorities can be mapped to the same PG.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]profile_idProfile Id.
[in]array_max(for "_get") Number of mappings allocated in pg_array
[out]pg_array(for "_set") Array of PFC priority to PG mapping
(for "_get") Array of PFC priority to PG mapping
[out]array_count(for "_set") Number of mappings in pg_array
(for "_get") Number of mappings returned

◆ bcm_cosq_priority_mapping_get_all()

int bcm_cosq_priority_mapping_get_all ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
int  index,
bcm_cosq_priority_mapping_t  type,
int  pri_max,
int *  pri_array,
int *  pri_count 
)

Get priority list attched to a priority group or service pool on a port.

CoSQ Priority Mapping Type Values
Type Description
bcmCosqPriorityGroup Priority Group
bcmCosqIngressPool Ingress Pool

This API is used to traverse all priority attached to a specific priority group or service pool on a port. When pri_max is zero or pri_array is null, pri_count will return the total cosq number attached to the port pg/port sp. pri_max specify the size of pri_array, if pri_max is smaller than actual priority number, pri_count would be the same as pri_max.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]gportGPORT ID
[in]indexService pool ID or Priority group ID, depends on the type value.
[in]typeType.(see BCM_COSQ_PRIORITY_MAPPING_table)
[in]pri_maxIndicate the cosq number user required.
[out]pri_arrayPriority list attached to the priority_group on the port, -1 is invalid value.
[out]pri_countIndicate cosq number returned. When pri_max is zero or pri_array is null, pri_count will return the total cosq number attached to the port pg/port sp.
Return values
BCM_E_NONE
BCM_E_PARAM
BCM_E_XXX

◆ bcm_cosq_safc_class_mapping_get()

int bcm_cosq_safc_class_mapping_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  port,
int  array_max,
bcm_cosq_safc_class_mapping_t *  mapping_array,
int *  array_count 
)

Get / set mapping of SAFC class to COSQs and / or scheduling nodes for a port.

Get or set mapping between SAFC class and COSQs and / or scheduling nodes for a port. Multiple mappings for a list of SAFC class can be set at one time. Each SAFC class can be mapped to multiple COSQs and / or scheduling nodes identified by gport id. Not all SAFC classes are needed. User only set a group of SAFC classes that system has to respond to. For \sc _get\ec, the number of SAFC class mappings associated with the port is returned by \sc array_count\ec. SAFC class and associated COSq priority or scheduling node's gport ID are returned respectively by class and gport_list in \sc mapping_array\ec. gport_list is ended by \sc BCM_GPORT_INVALID\ec, when retrieved gports does not full fill the list. If array_max<=0 and \sc mapping_array==NULL\ec, only array_count is returned.

#define BCM_COSQ_SAFC_GPORT_COUNT 20
// SAFC class to COSq / scheduling node mapping structure.
typedef struct bcm_cosq_safc_class_mapping_s {
int class_id; // SAFC class.
bcm_gport_t gport_list[BCM_COSQ_SAFC_GPORT_COUNT]; // mapped COSqs, -1 for no mapping.
} bcm_cosq_safc_class_mapping_t;
Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]portGPORT ID (BCM_GPORT_TYPE_MODPORT) or Logical port number
[in]array_max(for "_get") Number of mappings allocated in mapping_array
[out]mapping_array(for "_set") Array of SAFC class mappings
(for "_get") Array of SAFC class mappings
[out]array_count(for "_set") Number of mappings in mapping_array
(for "_get") Number of mappings returned

int class_id; // SAFC class.
bcm_gport_t gport_list[BCM_COSQ_SAFC_GPORT_COUNT]; // mapped COSqs, -1 for no mapping.
} bcm_cosq_safc_class_mapping_t;
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portGPORT ID (BCM_GPORT_TYPE_MODPORT) or Logical port number
[in]array_count(for "_set") Number of mappings in mapping_array
(for "_get") Number of mappings returned
[in]mapping_array(for "_set") Array of SAFC class mappings
(for "_get") Array of SAFC class mappings

◆ bcm_cosq_sched_config_get()

int bcm_cosq_sched_config_get ( int  unit,
int  weight_arr_size,
int *  weights,
int *  weight_arr_count,
int *  mode 
)

Get or set Class of Service policy, weights and delay.

Configure or retrieve the Class of Service policy, weights, and delay for a device or port. The mode options are listed in the table below. For modes which use weights, the weights may range between BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_MIN and the value of weight_max returned by bcm_cosq_sched_weight_max_get for the mode. If weight_max = BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_UNLIMITED, then any positive weight is acceptable. In BCM_COSQ_BOUNDED_DELAY mode, a negative value for an element of the weight array indicates that the weight and delay value for that Class of Service should remain unchanged, while the non-negative elements of the weight array are updated and assigned the given delay value. For modes which use weights, BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_STRICT may be supplied for some of the weights, indicating these queues should behave as in strict priority mode. Supported for chip BCM5698X. Note: In all devices supporting Enhanced Transmission Selection (ETS) hierarchical scheduling, bcm_cosq_sched_set and bcm_cosq_sched_get API is used to configure and retrieve the Class of Service policy, weights, and delay for CPU(CMIC) port only.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]weight_arr_sizeSize of the weights array
[out]weightsArray of relative weights indexed by CoS queue. The size of the array is specified in weight_arr_size
[out]weight_arr_countNumber of valid entries in the weights array
[out]modeScheduling mode, see table BCM_COSQ_table

◆ bcm_cosq_sched_get()

int bcm_cosq_sched_get ( int  unit,
int *  mode,
int  weights[BCM_COS_COUNT],
int *  delay 
)

Get or set Class of Service policy, weights and delay.

Configure or retrieve the Class of Service policy, weights, and delay for a device or port. The mode options are listed in the table below. For modes which use weights, the weights may range between BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_MIN and the value of weight_max returned by bcm_cosq_sched_weight_max_get for the mode. If weight_max = BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_UNLIMITED, then any positive weight is acceptable. In BCM_COSQ_BOUNDED_DELAY mode, a negative value for an element of the weight array indicates that the weight and delay value for that Class of Service should remain unchanged, while the non-negative elements of the weight array are updated and assigned the given delay value. For modes which use weights, BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_STRICT may be supplied for some of the weights, indicating these queues should behave as in strict priority mode. On the chips BCM5685x/BCM56750/BCM56830, the queues in strict priority mode must be in consecutive order. The chips BCM5644x/BCM5645x does not support the scheduling modes BCM_COSQ_WEIGHTED_FAIR_QUEUING and BCM_COSQ_BOUNDED_DELAY. Note: In all devices supporting Enhanced Transmission Selection (ETS) hierarchical scheduling, bcm_cosq_sched_set and bcm_cosq_sched_get API is used to configure and retrieve the Class of Service policy, weights, and delay for CPU(CMIC) port only.

BCM CoSQ Modes
Mode Description
BCM_COSQ_STRICT Highest priority packets always egress first. In this mode weight is ignored.
BCM_COSQ_ROUND_ROBIN Scheduling between queues uses a simple round robin algorithm. In this mode weight is ignored.
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHTED_ROUND_ROBIN Scheduling between queues uses a weighted round robin algorithm.
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHTED_FAIR_QUEUING Scheduling between queues uses a weighted fair queuing algorithm. Requires use of bcm_cosq_port_bandwidth_set for full configuration.
BCM_COSQ_BOUNDED_DELAY Scheduling between queues uses a weighted round robin algorithm with bounded time delay.
BCM_COSQ_DEFICIT_ROUND_ROBIN Scheduling between queues uses a deficit round robin algorithm.

BCM CoSQ Discrete Weight
Mode Description
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_DISCRETE_WEIGHT_LEVEL0 weight associated with level 0 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute.
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_DISCRETE_WEIGHT_LEVEL1 weight associated with level 1 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute.
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_DISCRETE_WEIGHT_LEVEL2 weight associated with level 2 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute.
BCM_COSQ_WEIGHT_DISCRETE_WEIGHT_LEVEL3 weight associated with level 3 of scheduler element having discrete weight attribute.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[out]modeScheduling mode, see table BCM_COSQ_table
[out]weightsArray of relative weights indexed by CoS queue. Use depends on the selected mode. See BCM_COSQ_COMBO . Note: Be aware that despite of BCM_COS_COUNT is 8, it supports up to 10 weights arrays in BCM5696x devices if and only if bcm_num_cos=10 is configured.
[out]delayUsed only if scheduling algorithm is BCM_COSQ_BOUNDED_DELAY to indicate the maximum amount of time before returning to the highest priority CoS queue. This value is only used for non-negative elements of the weights array.

BCM CoSQ Modes

BCM_COSQ_STRICT Highest priority packets always egress first. In this mode weight is ignored.

BCM_COSQ_WEIGHTED_ROUND_ROBIN Scheduling between queues uses a weighted round robin algorithm.

◆ bcm_cosq_schedq_mapping_get()

int bcm_cosq_schedq_mapping_get ( int  unit,
int  profile_index,
int  array_max,
bcm_cosq_mapping_t *  cosq_mapping_arr,
int *  size 
)

Setup cosq to mmu queue mapping profiles.

setup the cosq to mmu mapping for various profiles. Restrictions apply based on chip settings of number of unicast and multicast queues. Sum of num_ucq and num_mcq across all cos specified in cosq_mapping_arr should be equal to the number of UC/MC queues supported in current configuration. Profile can be modified only when there is no traffic egressing on any ports using this profile.

typedef struct bcm_cosq_mapping_s {
bcm_cos_queue_t cosq; // Cos value
int num_ucq; // Number of unicast queues. Valid values are 0-2
int num_mcq; // Number of multicast queues. Valid values are 0-1
int strict_priority; // Should be set to 1 for Minimum COS that could be using Strict Priority in future. This is used only for PFC receive mode setup and not for setting scheduler discipline. To setup scheduler discipline use \ref bcm_cosq_gport_sched_config_set
int fc_is_uc_only; // Use optimized PFC response only for UC queue mapped to the COS
} bcm_cosq_mapping_t;
Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number
[in]profile_indexProfile index
[in]array_max
[out]cosq_mapping_arr(for "_set") Cosq to mmu queue mapping array
(for "_get") Cosq to mmu queue mapping array
[out]size(for "_set") number of array elements
(for "_get") number of array elements

Configure the stat types for counters.

Configure or retrive the stat types. Configuring all 3 stat types from set 1 or set 2 is allowed. Configuring a mixture of stats from set1 and set3 or set 2 and set3 is allowed. Mixing of stat type in configuration from set 1 and set 2 is strictly prohibited. For the devices BCM5646x and BCM5626x, only the following stats are supported

Set Name Description
1 bcmCosqStatDroppedPackets Dropped packet count
1 bcmCosqStatYellowCongestionDroppedPackets Dropped yellow packets due to congestion
1 bcmCosqStatRedCongestionDroppedPackets Dropped red packets due to congestion
2 bcmCosqStatGreenDiscardDroppedPackets Dropped wred green packets
2 bcmCosqStatYellowDiscardDroppedPackets Dropped wred yellow packets
2 bcmCosqStatRedDiscardDroppedPackets Dropped wred red packets
2 bcmCosqStatDiscardDroppedPackets Dropped wred packets
3 bcmCosqStatOutPackets Transmit packet count

◆ bcm_cosq_stat_get()

int bcm_cosq_stat_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
bcm_cosq_stat_t  stat,
uint64 *  value 
)

Retrieve/set various MMU statistics based on stat type.

Retrieve/set various MMU statistics. The type bcm_cosq_stat_t is an enumeration of the available statistics. For "_get" functions, if the given cosq is -1, then the sum of the values of all the given port's CoS queues will be returned. For "_set" functions, if the given cosq is -1, the value of the port's first CoS queue will be set to the given value; the value of the port's all other CoS queues will be kept as untouched except for device BCM56620, on which the value of the port's all other CoS queues will be set to zero. When setting the non-zero value, if the device supports separate unicast and multicast queues, the value being set is evenly distributed between unicast and multicast counter. The "_set" functions don't apply to MMU threshold current/peak usage statistics, of which most are ended with current/peak suffix. BCM_E_PARAM will be returned when "_set" functions are operated againist such statistics. This is applicable to StrataXGS-III devices only.

bcm_cosq_stat_t
Name Description
bcmCosqStatDroppedPackets Dropped packet count, mainly for GPORT ID for queue group and scheduler gport. When GPORT ID indicates a physical port, a combined value for both unicast and multicast queues is retrieved.
bcmCosqStatDroppedBytes Dropped byte count, mainly for GPORT ID for queue group and scheduler gport. When GPORT ID indicates a physical port, a combined value for both unicast and multicast queues is retrieved.

◆ bcm_cosq_stat_get32()

int bcm_cosq_stat_get32 ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
bcm_cosq_stat_t  stat,
uint32 *  value 
)

Retrieve/set various MMU statistics based on stat type.

Retrieve/set various MMU statistics. The type bcm_cosq_stat_t is an enumeration of the available statistics. For "_get" functions, if the given cosq is -1, then the sum of the values of all the given port's CoS queues will be returned. For "_set" functions, if the given cosq is -1, the value of the port's first CoS queue will be set to the given value; the value of the port's all other CoS queues will be kept as untouched except for device BCM56620, on which the value of the port's all other CoS queues will be set to zero. When setting the non-zero value, if the device supports separate unicast and multicast queues, the value being set is evenly distributed between unicast and multicast counter. The "_set" functions don't apply to MMU threshold current/peak usage statistics, of which most are ended with current/peak suffix. BCM_E_PARAM will be returned when "_set" functions are operated againist such statistics. This is applicable to StrataXGS-III devices only.

◆ bcm_cosq_stat_set32()

int bcm_cosq_stat_set32 ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
bcm_cosq_stat_t  stat,
uint32  value 
)

Retrieve/set various MMU statistics based on stat type.

Retrieve/set various MMU statistics. The type bcm_cosq_stat_t is an enumeration of the available statistics. For "_get" functions, if the given cosq is -1, then the sum of the values of all the given port's CoS queues will be returned. For "_set" functions, if the given cosq is -1, the value of the port's first CoS queue will be set to the given value; the value of the port's all other CoS queues will be kept as untouched except for device BCM56620, on which the value of the port's all other CoS queues will be set to zero. When setting the non-zero value, if the device supports separate unicast and multicast queues, the value being set is evenly distributed between unicast and multicast counter. The "_set" functions don't apply to MMU threshold current/peak usage statistics, of which most are ended with current/peak suffix. BCM_E_PARAM will be returned when "_set" functions are operated againist such statistics. This is applicable to StrataXGS-III devices only.

◆ bcm_cosq_stat_sync_get()

int bcm_cosq_stat_sync_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  gport,
bcm_cos_queue_t  cosq,
bcm_cosq_stat_t  stat,
uint64 *  value 
)

Force an immediate counter update and retrieve various MMU statistics.

Similar to bcm_cosq_stat_get(), value returned is software accumulated counter synced with the hardware counter. On the chip BCM56960, for stat bcmCosqStatOutPackets/bcmCosqStatOutBytes because of clear on read implementation in hardware, bcm_cosq_stat_sync_get on OutPackets will have impact on OutBytes counters and vice-versa. Hence recommendation is to use bcm_stat_sync(unit) api before the bcm_cosq_stat_get API instead of using bcm_cosq_stat_sync_get API.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]gportGPORT ID.
[in]cosqCoS Queue.
[in]statStatistic to be retrieved. See table BCM_COSQ_STAT_table .
[out]value(for "_get") statistic value.
(for "_set") statistic value.

◆ bcm_cosq_subport_flow_control_get()

int bcm_cosq_subport_flow_control_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  subport,
bcm_gport_t *  sched_port 
)

Set/Get a node to be flow controlled when a flow control packet is recevied.

This API is used for implementing Channelization over Ethernet (CoE) and sets the mapping of a subport and associated subport tag to a node (Port, L0, L1, L2) to be flow controlled when a flow control packet is received on the subport with the identifying subport tag. This API should be invoked after fabric ports and internal ports are created and their mapping to switch ports is established. Appropriate packet matching MUST be configured via bcm_port_congestion_config_set such that the system can identify flow control packets.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]subportSubport to associate with sched_port
[out]sched_port(for "_set") Node to be flow controlled
(for "_get") Node to be flow controlled

◆ bcm_cosq_subport_flow_control_set()

◆ bcm_cosq_tas_profile_commit()

int bcm_cosq_tas_profile_commit ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  port,
bcm_cosq_tas_profile_id_t  pid 
)

Commit the TAS profile.

Commit the profile to indicate the profile is ready to write to hardware. Calendar entry auto adjustment will be proceed in bcm_cosq_tas_profile_commit when the spn_TAS_CALENDAR_AUTO_ADJUST_FOR_TXOVERRUN or spn_TAS_CALENDAR_AUTO_ADJUST_FOR_HOLDADVANCE is specified. When Tx overrun (the transmission gate associated with a queue has closed and a frame that originated from the queue is still being transmitted) happens, TAS functionality will be impacted in the next hop. Delay parameters inside chip are required to be considered when programming the calendar entries to avoid TX overrun after gate closure. The sum of all the delays caused by different pipes is called Gate Close Response Time or Tgcr. The value specified in spn_TAS_CALENDAR_AUTO_ADJUST_REF_MAXSDU would be referenced to compose the device delay parameters Tgcr. NOTE: the value of spn_TAS_CALENDAR_AUTO_ADJUST_REF_MAXSDU is only provide the information(queueMaxSDU) to calculte the delay parameters, SDK won't program any MTU constrain according to this soc property. (Assume frames exceeding queueMaxSDU will be filtered out) When preemption(IEEE 802.1Qbu) is active and spn_TAS_CALENDAR_AUTO_ADJUST_FOR_HOLDADVANCE is specified, the entry adjustment would consider the holdAdvance time and the proper holdRequest configuration would be reflected to hold the preemptable traffic.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]port
[in]pidprofile id

◆ bcm_cosq_tcb_buffer_multi_get()

int bcm_cosq_tcb_buffer_multi_get ( int  unit,
bcm_cosq_buffer_id_t  buffer_id,
int  array_max,
bcm_cosq_tcb_buffer_t *  buffer_array,
int *  array_count 
)

Get packet records in TCB buffer.

Get packet records sampled before and after a packet drop event. This could only be used when TCB is in FREEZE state. When array_max is 0, buffer_array is null, array_count will return the actual record number in TCB buffer. Packet record format is as below:

// TCB Pkt Structure.
typedef struct bcm_cosq_tcb_buffer_s {
uint64 timestamp; // timestamp
bcm_gport_t ingress_gport; // ingress port gport.
bcm_gport_t egress_gport; // egress egress gport.
bcm_gport_t queue; // Egress UC queue gport
uint32 queue_size; // Queue size bytes
uint32 service_pool_size; // Service pool size bytes
uint8 buf_data[80]; // The first 80 bytes of captured packet
} bcm_cosq_tcb_buffer_t;
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]buffer_idTCB buffer id.
[in]array_maxNumber of elements allocated in buffer_array.
[out]buffer_arrayArray of packet records.
[out]array_countActual number of packet records returned in buffer_array.

◆ bcm_cosq_tcb_config_t_init()

void bcm_cosq_tcb_config_t_init ( bcm_cosq_tcb_config_t *  config)

Initialize a tcb config structure.

Initialize a tcb config structure.

typedef struct bcm_cosq_tcb_config_s {
bcm_cosq_tcb_scope_t scope_type; // TCB monitor scope type
bcm_gport_t gport; // Logical port or GPORT ID
bcm_cos_queue_t cosq; // Cos queue, reserved field
uint32 trigger_reason; // Drop event trigger reason
uint32 pre_freeze_capture_num; // Number of capture transactions before freeze
uint32 pre_freeze_capture_time; // Capture time before freeze, usec unit
uint32 post_sample_probability; // sample probability at post stage, step is 1/16, valid configure range is 1 C 16, 1 means 1/16 sample, 16 means sample all
uint32 pre_sample_probability; // sample probability at pre stage, step is 1/16, valid configure range is 1 C 16, 1 means 1/16 sample, 16 means sample all
int pipe_id; // Pipe id
} bcm_cosq_tcb_config_t;

TCB monitor scope type
Name Purpose
bcmCosqTcbScopeUcastQueue Set scope to a unicast queue
bcmCosqTcbScopeIngressPort Set scope to ingress port
bcmCosqTcbScopeEgressPort Set scope to egress port
bcmCosqTcbScopeIngressPipe Set scope to ingress pipe
bcmCosqTcbScopeEgressPipe Set scope to egress pipe
bcmCosqTcbScopeMaxCount Must be the last

trigger_reason is used to configure the drop event trigger reason, 4 types are available. Multiple reasons could be enabled at the same time.

// TCB Track Trigger Reason
#define BCM_COSQ_TCB_INGRESS_ADMIN_DROP 0x0001 // Ingress admission drop
#define BCM_COSQ_TCB_EGRESS_ADMIN_DROP 0x0002 // Egress admission drop
#define BCM_COSQ_TCB_WRED_DROP 0x0004 // Weighted random drop
#define BCM_COSQ_TCB_CFAP_DROP 0x0008 // Cell free allocations pool drop
Parameters
[in,out]configPointer to TCB configuration structure to initialize.
Return values
NONE.

◆ bcm_cosq_tcb_control_get()

int bcm_cosq_tcb_control_get ( int  unit,
int  buffer_id,
bcm_cosq_tcb_control_t  type,
int *  arg 
)

Set/get TCB working status.

Available control type are BCM_COSQ_TCB_CONTROL_TYPE_table When control type is bcmCosqTcbControlEnable, argument with value 1 means enable, 0 means disable. All TCB configuration can only be changed when TCB is disabled. When control type is bcmCosqTcbControlFreeze, argument with value 1 means freeze, 0 means restart.Buffer_id with an invalid value -1 could be used to freeze and restart all TCB buffers at a once.

TCB Control Type
Type Description
bcmCosqTcbControlEnable Enable or disable TCB.
bcmCosqTcbControlFreeze Freeze or restart TCB.
bcmCosqTcbControlMaxCount Must be the last
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]buffer_idTCB buffer id
[in]typePointer to profile index.
[in,out]arg(for "_set") Control argument.
(for "_get") Control argument.

◆ bcm_cosq_tcb_event_multi_get()

int bcm_cosq_tcb_event_multi_get ( int  unit,
bcm_cosq_buffer_id_t  buffer_id,
int  array_max,
bcm_cosq_tcb_event_t *  event_array,
int *  array_count,
int *  overflow_count 
)

Get drop event records in TCB buffer.

Get all drop event records when a packet drop occurs. This could only be used when TCB is in FREEZE state. When array_max is 0, event_array is null, array_count will return the actual record number in TCB buffer. If the array_count is not 0, but the data of several entries are empty, it may be caused by SER correction. Drop event record format is as below:

typedef struct bcm_cosq_tcb_event_s {
uint64 timestamp; // timestamp
bcm_gport_t ingress_gport; // ingress gport.
bcm_gport_t egress_gport; // egress gport.
bcm_gport_t queue; // Egress queue gport
uint32 queue_size; // Queue depth
uint32 service_pool_size; // Service pool depth
uint32 drop_reason; // Drop reason vector
bcm_color_t color; // Packet color
} bcm_cosq_tcb_event_t;
Parameters
[in]unitBCM device number.
[in]buffer_idTCB buffer id.
[in]array_maxNumber of elements allocated in event_array.
[out]event_arrayArray of drop event records.
[out]array_countActual number of packet records returned in event_array.
[out]overflow_countCount of drop events exceeding the event buffer storage.

◆ bcm_cosq_tcb_threshold_profile_create()

int bcm_cosq_tcb_threshold_profile_create ( int  unit,
int  flags,
bcm_cosq_buffer_id_t  buffer_id,
bcm_cosq_tcb_threshold_profile_t *  threshold,
int *  profile_index 
)

Create tcb threshold profile.

Create a threshold profile for a specified TCB. The available flags for creation are BCM_COSQ_TCB_PROFILE_CREATE_f The profile_index could be created and returned by API. User should specify a profile_index when BCM_COSQ_TCB_THRESHOLD_PROFILE_WITH_ID flag is set. When BCM_COSQ_TCB_THRESHOLD_PROFILE_UPDATE is set, BCM_COSQ_TCB_THRESHOLD_PROFILE_WITH_ID should also be set, the threshole profile with specified profile_index will be updated. For threshold profile, start threshold should bigger than stop threshold.

TCB Profile Create Flags
Flag Description
BCM_COSQ_TCB_THRESHOLD_PROFILE_WITH_ID Create a threshold profile with a specified id.
BCM_COSQ_TCB_THRESHOLD_PROFILE_UPDATE Update an existing threshold profile.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]flagsTCB threshold profile create flags.
[in]buffer_idTCB buffer id
[in]thresholdTCB configuration
[in,out]profile_index(IN/OUT) Pointer to profile index.

void bcm_cosq_tcb_threshold_profile_t_init ( bcm_cosq_tcb_threshold_profile_t *  threshold)

Initialize a tcb threshold profile structure.

Initialize a tcb threshold profile structure.

typedef struct bcm_cosq_tcb_threshold_profile_s {
uint32 start_threshold_bytes; // The start threshold above which queue start the capture.
uint32 stop_threshold_bytes; // The stop threshold below which queue stop the capture.
} bcm_cosq_tcb_threshold_profile_t;
Parameters
[in,out]thresholdPointer to TCB threshold profile structure to initialize.

This is used by the application to register/unregister the callback routine that needs to be called when we encounter the OBM drop/overflow interrupts.

int unit,
struct *bcm_obm_interrupt_info_t,
void *user_data);
typedef enum bcm_obm_interrupt_type_s
{
bcmObmInterruptTypeExpressOverflow = 1 ,
bcmObmInterruptTypeExpressDrop = 2 ,
bcmObmInterruptTypePreemptOverflow = 3 ,
bcmObmInterruptTypePreemptDrop = 4 ,
bcmObmInterruptTypeMax
}bcm_obm_interrupt_type_t
